<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT: PLA Troops Take Up Defense Duties in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The national flag of the People's
Republic of China was hoisted simultaneously at zero hour today at
the Tamar Barracks and 13 other barracks in Hong Kong by the
advance troops of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) Garrison.
</P>
<P>
This symbolizes the official commencement of defense duties in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region by the PLA Hong Kong
Garrison as well as the end of a 100-odd-year history without
Chinese troops stationed on this part of Chinese soil.
</P>
<P>
A while ago, a key-handover ceremony symbolic of the transfer
of defense duties was held between the advance troops of the PLA
Hong Kong Garrison and the outgoing British troops.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
