<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Gala Party Celebrating Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The little boom town of shenzhen
neighboring on Hong Kong turned out today to be a sea of people,
an ocean of flags and flowers and the jubilant scene of dancing
lions.
</P>
<P>
At 18:00 p.m., crowds of people thronged towards the 3.6-km
long road from Lianhuashan to Huanggang Port to see off the
advance team of soliders to be stationed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
As 39 truck-loads of soliders dressed in grass green uniform
were driving by, the crowds lining the road waved and cheered,
bidding good-bye to the graceful, proud soliders of the advance
team.
</P>
<P>
As night fell, hundreds of thousands of people gathered on the
beautifully decorated major thoroughfare from Overseas Chinese
Town in the east to Huangbeiling in the west of the city, the
first Special Economic Zone in China and vanguard in the opening
up drive, to celebrate the moment of Hong Kong handover.
</P>
<P>
At 23:20 p.m., more than 1,000 fireworks boomed into the sky
from the Honghu Park amidst thunderous sound, lifting the curtain
of a fireworks gala party celebrating the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to the party organizer, more than 100,000 fireworks
in 1997 varieties were fired throughout the 70-minute gala party
in the Honghu Park, which was attended by more than 10,000
people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
