<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Resumes Exercise of Sovereignty Over Hong Kong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- At the zero hour of July 1, 1997,
the Hong Kong handover ceremony was being held at the new annex of
the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese five-star national flag was slowly hoisted to the
top of the flagpole where the Union Jack fluttered about a minute
before, marking the end of more than 150 years of British colonial
rule in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, Britain's
Prince Charles, Prime Minister Tony Blair and other members from
both the Chinese and British delegations attended the historic
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the event, President Jiang said that the return of
Hong Kong to the motherland shows that the development of Hong
Kong had entered a new period from that moment on.
</P>
<P>
"After the return of Hong Kong, the Chinese government will
implement the basic principles of `one country, two systems',
`Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong', and a high degree of
autonomy, maintain the original social, economic and living styles
of Hong Kong, and keep the laws of Hong Kong basically unchanged,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from more than 40 countries and regions and over 30
international and regional organizations, consul generals of
various countries in Hong Kong, representatives of overseas
Chinese and people of Chinese descent, and Hong Kong people from
all walks of life attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the transfer ceremony of the defense duties was also
held between the vanguard of the garrison of Chinese People's
Liberation Army troops and the garrison of British troops in their
barracks.
</P>
<P>
The crest of the British Royal family on the collar badges and
shoulder straps of customs officers and policemen in Hong Kong was
replaced by Bauhinia flowers, the symbol of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
