<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Map Indicates New Boundary Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The region's present northeast boundary line runs between the
Dapeng peninsula on the side of Guangdong and Ping Chau islet on
the side of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether 35 points along the boundary line which
was agreed on between Guangdong and Hong Kong through
consultations prior to June 30. The readjustment of a few spots in
the new map is "for the convenience of administration and
navigation", the officials explained.
</P>
<P>
The standard official map of HKSAR has been drawn up by the
State Bureau of Surveying and Mapping in three versions, with
scales of 1:100,000, 1:500,000 and 1:750,000, and in two languages
-- Chinese and English.
</P>
<P>
Any map with the boundary line between Guangdong Province and
Hong Kong not in conformity with the new HKSAR map will be invalid
after July 1, the officials noted.
</P>
<P>
The larger map is available at the State Bureau of Surveying
and Mapping. Two smaller versions designed for news media's use
can be obtained from the Office of Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
under the State Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
