<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Resumes Exercise of Sovereignty over Hong Kong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong has been China's territory since ancient times.
Britain established colonial rule in Hong Kong away by forcing the
government of the Qing Dynasty to sign three unequal treaties in
1842, 1860 and 1898.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, the governments of China and Britain signed a joint
declaration on the Hong Kong question, which proclaims that the
Chinese government will resume the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
All of China has been bustling with activity in anticipation of
the day that would put an end to more than 100 years of national
humiliation. Lanterns and colored streamers are hanging in shops
and office buildings, and various celebrations have been held to
exhibit the Chinese people's pride.
</P>
<P>
People throughout the country marked the great event in a
variety of festive activities, many staying up all night to watch
live TV broadcasts of the historic handover.
</P>
<P>
In the capital, the enthusiasm of the crowd of 100,000 turned
Tiananmen Square into a sea of revelry.
</P>
<P>
Only one minute before the zero hour of July 1, many people
stood to the east of the square facing the digital countdown clock
ticking off the seconds until Hong Kong's return. They chanted in
unison from 60 to 1.
</P>
<P>
When the board showed all zeros, the cheers of the jubilant
crowd mingled with the swelling sounds of music which could be
heard miles away.
</P>
<P>
At Jinghai Temple in the city of Nanjing, where the unequal
Nanking Treaty to cede Hong Kong was negotiated, people took the
155th and final strike on the "Warning Bell" at the zero hour of
July 1, symbolizing the end of 155 years of national humiliation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Troops Take Up Defense Duties in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The national flag of the People's
Republic of China (PRC) was hoisted at zero hour today over the
Tamar Barracks, signaling to the world that the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) troops have officially taken over defense
duties in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A solemn flag-hoisting ceremony was held at 23:58'50 on June 30
at the site of the former headquarters of the British Forces in
Hong Kong at Tamar, also known as the Prince of Wales Barracks,
which was brightly lit.
</P>
<P>
At zero hour on July 1 (Beijing time), the national anthem of
the People's Republic of China was played, while three soldiers
hoisted the national flag. More than 100 officers and men of PLA
ground, naval and air forces lined up in formation and stood in
salute to the fluttering five-star red flag.
</P>
<P>
At 23:58 on June 30, the Chinese and British sides held a
simple defense duties handover ceremony, with 22 officers and
soldiers from each side participating.
</P>
<P>
After the hoisting of the national flag, Major General Xiong
Ziren, political commissar of the PLA Hong Kong Garrison, said in
a brief address, "The sacred moment which the Chinese nation
yearned for so long has arrived, and we hoist the red flag over
Hong Kong now."
</P>
<P>
He noted that this historic moment marks the complete end of a
156- year history of humiliation for Hong Kong, and signals the
Chinese government's resumption of its exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, this also signifies that the PLA Hong Kong
Garrison has taken up defense duties in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, and started to implement the sacred mission
entrusted by the people of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"We will conscientiously implement the principle of 'one
country, two systems', keep our mission in mind, live up to
people's expectation, remain always loyal to the motherland,
strictly perform our defense duties, and resolutely safeguard the
sovereignty and dignity of the motherland and the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called on his troops to step up army building in an
all-round way, so as to keep raising the capabilities to perform
defense duties and keep up the good image of a powerful and
civilized army in line with the instructions of Chairman Jiang
Zemin of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday evening, the British troops held a "sunset" or
farewell ceremony at Tamar East and lowered the Union Jack.
</P>
<P>
Flag-raising ceremonies were held in 13 other barracks taken
over by the PLA Hong Kong Garrison, including those at
Stonecutters Island, Gun Club Hill, Shek Kong and Stanley.
</P>
<P>
The Tamar Barracks is centered around the 28-story building,
which, built in 1979, served as the headquarters of the British
Forces in Hong Kong. Tamar was named after a British warship,
which landed the British forces on Hong Kong Island in 1841.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT 14: Economic Interests of All Countries to be Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said that the legitimate economic
interests of all countries and regions in Hong Kong will be
protected by law.
</P>
<P>
After the return, Hong Kong will retain its status of a free
port, continue to function as an international financial, trade
and shipping center, and maintain and develop its economic and
cultural ties with other countries, regions and relevant
international organizations, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that all countries and regions that have investment and
trade interests here will continue to work for the prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
