<HEADLINE> HK to Maintain its Role After Handover: Swedish FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's role as Sweden's
base of investment in Southeast Asia and China's inland areas will
not be weakened and Sweden will remain in Hong Kong like other
countries, Swedish Foreign Minister Lena Hjelm-Wallen said in a
newspaper interview published today.
</P>
<P>
Dagens Industri newspaper published the interview in today's
special issue marking Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
In the interview, Hjelm-Wallen said she was confident that Hong
Kong's role as the trade and financial center would be maintained
after the handover.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's future depends primarily on the development of
China's inland areas, especially the economic development of the
inland areas, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
To maintain Hong Kong's present prosperity and present social
system was obviously in the interest of the Chinese government and
was important to the development of the country itself, she said.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, Hong Kong will continue to function as a fast
developing commercial center and a gateway to China, and its role
will not be changed after China resumes its exercise of
sovereignty there," the minister said. 
</P>
