<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Byelection Held Smoothly in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The By-election in Manikganj-3
constituency in central Bangladesh ended peacefully today with a
high voter turnout despite rainy weather.
</P>
<P>
Six candidates were in the race for the seat, which was vacated
by the death of the opposition lawmaker Nizamuddin Khan in March.
The final result, however, was not available now.
</P>
<P>
Voting passed off without any disruption at all the 91 polling
centers.
</P>
<P>
According to Deputy Commissioner of Manikganj Abdur Razzak, no
incidents of violence were reported and no allegations of
irregularities or rigging were raised or lodged to the Election
Commission by any political party or candidate.
</P>
<P>
Candidates from the major political parties all expressed their
satisfaction at the measures taken to ensure the byelection was
held in a free and fair manner, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 officials were involved in the conducting of the
byelection and nearly 3,000 members of law enforcing agencies were
deployed to maintain security at the polling centers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
