<HEADLINE> Urgent: Inauguration &AMP; Swearing-in Ceremony to Start Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The ceremony for the inauguration
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and the
swearing-in of the HKSAR government will begin at 01:30 AM at the
Extension to the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (CEC).
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 representatives and guests from all parts of
the world, who have just attended the Hong Kong handover ceremony,
will attend the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 reporters holding special permits for on-the-spot
coverage of the coming event arrived at a designated area hours
ago and have made all necessary preparations.
</P>
<P>
At the front of the main hall, where the ceremony will be held,
hang a five-star red flag and the regional flag of the HKSAR
featuring a bauhinia. In front of the rostrum are hundreds of pots
of bright-colored flowers. The hall has a solemn atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Two giant TV screens flanking the rostrum will show ceremony
proceedings live. People in all parts of the world will witness
live TV broadcasts of ceremony proceedings.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, subjected to 156 years of British colonial rule,
will enter a new era of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong"
after Tung Chee Hwa, the Chief Executive of the HKSAR, and other
HKSAR government officials, who are all Hong Kong residents, have
been sworn in.  
</P>
</TEXT>
