<HEADLINE> urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Ceremony Starts (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ceremony for the inauguration of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) and the swearing-in of the HKSAR
government started at 1:30 AM today.
</P>
<P>
When Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen proclaimed the opening of
the ceremony, all people present stood up and the military band
struck up the national anthem of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR will be formally established at today's ceremony.
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the HKSAR, and other HKSAR
government officials, who are all Hong Kong residents, will be
sworn in at the ceremony. Hong Kong, subjected to 156 years of
British colonial rule, will from then on enter a new era of "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong."
</P>
