<HEADLINE> Urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Jiang Proclamation (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin solemnly proclaims at the HKSAR
inauguration and HKSAR government swearing-in ceremony: "I hereby
declare the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR) of the People's Republic of China."
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin's proclamation is followed by long, enthusiastic
applause.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the HKSAR signifies that the great concept
of "one country, two systems" put forward by the late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping has become a reality. For Hong Kong, it marks
the start of a new era of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong,"
which was subjected to British colonial rule for 156 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
