<HEADLINE> Urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Swearing-in of Principal Officials (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 23 principal officials of the government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) have been sworn in at the
ceremony for the inauguration of the HKSAR and the swearing-in of
the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
The proceedings are supervised by Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
The 23 principal officials, standing in front of the rostrum
with their faces turned to the national flag and the regional flag
of the HKSAR and their right hand raised, and led by
Administrative Secretary Chan Fang On-sang, swear: We pledge to
uphold the Basic Law of the HKSAR of the People's Republic of
China (PRC), be loyal to the HKSAR of the PRC, fulfill our
official duties faithfully, abide by laws, be clean and honest,
and serve the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The majority of these officials had held posts in the British
Hong Kong government. As representatives of the 180,000 civil
servants in Hong Kong, the fact that they work for the HKSAR in
their original posts has been regarded as an indication of Hong
Kong's smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa has been sworn in a moment
earlier.
</P>
</TEXT>
