<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Night-long Carnival To Welcome Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The whole nation opened its heart
to welcome Hong Kong home, with a dusk-to-dawn celebration on
Tiananmen Square in the capital of Beijing tonight.
</P>
<P>
"The Beijing citizens will go all out to support prosperity and
stability in Hong Kong. We will join hands with Hong Kong people
to create a more beautiful future," Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin told
a cheering crowd of 100,000 on the square.
</P>
<P>
Tiananmen Square was ablaze with hundreds of floodlights and
red lanterns for one of the biggest festivities of the
century. The square is decorated with 30,000 pots of flowers and
the trees around the square are festooned with colorful lights.
</P>
<P>
"I told my students a lot about Hong Kong's past. But today, a
new page of history is unrolling before our eyes," said Xu Yanqin,
a middle school history teacher.
</P>
<P>
A student from Beijing University said, "It is hard to imagine
that we could see Hong Kong coming home today if China had not
opened up to the outside world and adopted the 'one country, two
systems' policy that allows Hong Kong to maintain the existing
capitalist system and lifestyle."
</P>
<P>
At about midnight, dozens of men, each with a red scarf wrapped
around his head, beat huge drums in a thundering fashion while
1,997 displays of fireworks emblazoned the summer sky. The crowd
of 100,000 counted down in unison the last 10 seconds of British
colonial rule in the east.
</P>
<P>
And at the zero hour of July 1, they watched the raising of the
Chinese national flag in Hong Kong televised on five huge screens
on the square, singing the Chinese national anthem.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's future will be brighter because it has a unique
position in China's reform, opening up and modernization drive," a
government employee said.
</P>
<P>
She participated in the musical performance "Beijing Bless You,
Hong Kong" held on the stage on the east side of the square.
</P>
<P>
"Maintaining the stability and prosperity of Hong Kong is a
historic trend that we must follow," Mayor Jia Qinglin said.
</P>
<P>
The sound of favorite national songs echoed throughout the
spacious square as the crowd danced in a grand spectacle of
patriotic fervor.
</P>
<P>
"I feel exited to have the opportunity to witness Hong Kong's
return to the embrace of the motherland on this square in
Beijing," said Xu, a Hong Kong businessman who flew here from Hong
Kong to attend the celebration.
</P>
<P>
"I have full confidence in the future of Hong Kong, because the
Special Administrative Region will be run under the guideline
of 'one country, two systems' that Deng Xiaoping put forward," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The celebration will end after the national flag is raised on
the square at about 5:00 a.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
