<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Swearing-in of Law Makers (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) have been worn in
at the ceremony for the inauguration of the HKSAR and the
swearing-in of the HKSAR government. The swearing-in is supervised
by HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
The members of the PLC, standing in front of the rostrum, with
their faces turned towards the national flag of the People's
Republic of China (PRC) and the regional flag of the HKSAR and
with their right hand raised, and led by PLC President Rita Fan
Hsu Lai-tai, take an oath of office, pledging to uphold the Basic
Law of the HKSAR of the PRC, be loyal to the HKSAR of the PRC, be
dedicated to their duties, abide by laws, be honest and clean,
and serve the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The PLC members, elected in December 1996, are responsible for
enacting laws that are necessary for enforcement in the HKSAR
before the formation of the first Legislative Council of the HKSAR
a year later.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa, principal
officials of the HKSAR government and members of the Executive
Council of the HKSAR have been sworn in separately. The executive
and legislative departments of the HKSAR are composed entirely of
Hong Kong residents. This is a demonstration of the policy of
"Hong Kong People governing Hong Kong."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
