<HEADLINE> Urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Swearing-in of Judges (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 34 judges of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) have been sworn in at the ceremony for the inauguration of
the HKSAR and the swearing-in of the HKSAR government under the
supervision of HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
Led by Chief Justice Li Kwok-nang, the 34 judges, with their
right hand raised and facing the national flag of the People's
Republic of China (PRC) and the regional flag of the HKSAR, take
the vow that they will uphold the Basic Law of the HKSAR of the
PRC, be loyal to the HKSAR of the PRC, perform their official
duties faithfully, abide by laws, be honest and clean, and serve
the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
They stress in particular "to safeguard the rule of law and
uphold justice with the spirit of fearlessness, impartiality,
selflessness honesty."
</P>
<P>
The newly-established HKSAR enjoys independent judicial power,
including that of final adjudication.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the HKSAR,
principal officials of the HKSAR government, members of the
Executive Council of the HKSAR, and members of the Provisional
Legislative Council of the HKSAR have all been sworn in.
</P>
</TEXT>
