<HEADLINE> Japanese Parties Pleased at Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Japanese political parties today
spoke highly of Hong Kong's return to China and expressed their
confidence that Hong Kong's prosperity and development will
continue.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the Liberal Democratic Party Koichi Kato
said Japan, as an Asian state, wants to express its joy over Hong
Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Japan hopes the great experiment on the "one country, two
systems" formula will succeed and the luster of a free and open
Hong Kong will never disappear, said Koichi.
</P>
<P>
The Social Democratic Party said Hong Kong's return marked the
end of colonial rule as the world moved to the 21st century,
opening a new page in the human history.
</P>
<P>
The New Frontier Party said Hong Kong's return to China put a
period to the modern history of Asia. It hoped Hong Kong would
enjoy a high degree of autonomy and maintain its prosperity and
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Communist Party said Hong Kong's return to China
declared the end of the colonial rule in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
