<HEADLINE> Urgent: HKSAR Inauguration, Speech by Premier (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng gives a speech at the ceremony for the
inauguration of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) and the swearing-in of the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
Li extends, on behalf of the Central People's Government, warm
congratulations on the establishment of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
He expresses the hope that the first Chief Executive of the
HKSAR and the HKSAR government would implement the Basic Law of
the HKSAR in earnest, fulfill their duties with dedication and
meet expectations of the people at their respective posts in the
spirit of love for China and for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He says that the Central Government will give full support to
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and the HKSAR Government in the
performance of their duties.
</P>
<P>
He says he is convinced that Hong Kong compatriots, now back in
the embrace of the motherland, will contribute to Hong Kong's
continued long-term prosperity and stability with their industry
and wisdom.
</P>
<P>
He says, "The return of Hong Kong to the motherland and the
establishment of the Government of HKSAR mark the successful
application of Deng Xiaoping's great vision of "one country, two
systems" in resolving the question of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"It represents an immense success of the Chinese people in
their pursuit for complete national reunification. At the same
time it is a major contribution to the cause of universal peace
and progress. Hong Kong has now entered a new historical era and
its future will be even more splendid."
</P>
<P>
Li's speech wins long and warm applause from the audience.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration ceremony started at 1:30 AM today. After
Chinese President Jiang Zemin proclaimed the establishment of the
HKSAR, chief executive Tung Chee Hwa, 23 principal officials of
the HKSAR government, 14 members of the HKSAR Executive Council,
members of the HKSAR Provisional Legislative Council and 34 judges
of the HKSAR were sworn in.
</P>
