<HEADLINE> Excerpt of Speech by Chief Executive at HKSAR Inauguration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- After 156 years of separation,
Hong Kong and China is whole again, the first Chief Executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa
said here at dawn today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony for the inauguration of the HKSAR and
the swearing-in of the HKSAR Government, Tung said, "We are here
today to say to the world: Hong Kong has entered into a new era."
</P>
<P>
The resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
under "one country, two systems" is an extraordinary concept, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The scope and comprehensiveness of this groundbreaking model
(China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
under the "one country, two systems" principle) is the first of
its kind in the history of the world. Hong Kong, under the eyes of
the world, will proudly pioneer such a challenge, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have no doubt, however, that Hong Kong will overcome these
challenges and build an even better tomorrow," he said.
</P>
<P>
"For the first time in history, we, the people of Hong Kong,
will shape our own destiny. The SAR Government is fully committed
to preserving the Hong Kong way of life, maintaining Hong Kong's
free and open economic system, upholding the rule of law, and
building a more democratic and participative society," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will be compassionate to those in need, and we will
maintain Hong Kong as a vibrant, international, and cosmopolitan
hub," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said he will perform, in great dedication, the sacred duty
entrusted by law and lead the pioneering Hong Kong people on their
march along the road of "one country, two systems".  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
