<HEADLINE> Botswanan President Begins Visit to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- President Ketumile Masire
of Botswana arrived here this morning for a five-day state visit
to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
President Masire, who has been a proponent for regional
co-operation, this afternoon held talks with Tanzanian President
Mkapa on bilateral relation between the two countries. Both
Botswana and Tanzania are members of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC).
</P>
