<HEADLINE> Guangzhou People Celebrate Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 30,000 people gathered
at a city stadium in Guangzhou, the capital of southern Guangdong
Province, to celebrate the historic even of Hong Kong's return to
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Beautifully decorated with flowers, flags, banners and
lanterns, the whole city was deeply immersed in festivity.
</P>
<P>
"I felt immensely proud that Hong Kong is returning to the
motherland and the traces of 150-year disgrace will be erased
completely," said Zhong Nanshan, a professor from the city's
medical institute, in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
In the stadium, where the gala party was held, a variety of
performances, including songs and dances were staged. Among them
was the dance "Hong Kong Tomorrow", which depicts a prosperous
Hong Kong in the future.
</P>
<P>
The solo presented by famous Guangzhou opera performer Huang
Jieyi sang praises of patriotism exhibited by the ancient Chinese
people in the fight against British invaders.
</P>
<P>
Wei Lianjian, a descendent of an anti-British hero in the Qing
Dynasty, said:"One hundred years ago, our ancestors fought
gallantly against the British imperialists; today, we should
remember the history and make greater contributions to a more
powerful and prosperous motherland."
</P>
<P>
The mosting exciting moment came when the countdown clock
ticked down towards zero. People in the stadium shouted in chorus,
"five, four, three, two, one" before bursting into cheers and
excitement.
</P>
<P>
In the waves of cheers, Huang Guocheng, a Hong Kong resident who
has come to invest in inland areas since the late 1970s, told
Xinhua, "As Chinese, I feel proud that Hong Kong has at last
returned to the embrace of the motherland."
</P>
<P>
"With the strong backing of the motherland, I am convinced that
Hong Kong will become all the more stable, more prosperous, and
more closely linked to the inland areas," he added. 
</P>
