<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets with Prince Charles in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met with Prince Charles here tonight in the Hong Kong Convention
and Exhibition Center Extension.
</P>
<P>
He said that the smooth settlement of the Hong Kong question
marked a successful application of Deng Xiaoping's great concept
of "one country, two systems", and is the result of the joint
efforts by both Chinese and British sides. It is in the interest
of both China and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Both Jiang and Charles arrived here for the Hong Kong handover
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said that he was very delighted to be able to
co-officiate the Hong Kong handover ceremony with Prince Charles.
</P>
<P>
Prince Charles said that he was also delighted to meet with
President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said that Britain has always had a special relationship with
China and Hong Kong, and is willing to continue to maintain and
develop this kind of relationship.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said that the great concept of "one country,
two systems" is by no means an expedient measure, but a
far-reaching consideration oriented with China's reunification and
is therefore in the fundamental interest of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return, he said, the Chinese government will
unswervingly implement the principle of "one country, two
systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree
of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
"We are full of confidence in Hong Kong's long-term prosperity
and stability," he said. "Hong Kong will continue to play its
special role as a window, bridge and channel in China's opening to
the outside world," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that with the smooth transfer of Hong Kong, the
problem between China and Britain left over from history has been
solved. He expressed the hope that a new good beginning will be
made in the Sino-British relationship.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang also asked Prince Charles to convey his
greetings to Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II.
</P>
<P>
Prince Charles expressed his thanks to President Jiang, and
said that Her Majesty had paid a visit to China, which had left a
very good impression on her.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng and British Prime Minister Tony Blair
were present at the meeting. Both of them expressed the hope that
after Hong Kong returns to China, the Sino-British relationship
will have a new starting point for further development.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, vice chairman of the Central
Military Commission Zhang Wannian, State Councilor and secretary
general of the State Council Luo Gan, Director of the Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch Zhou Nan, and first Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa 
</P>
</TEXT>
