<HEADLINE> Southwest Municipality Hails Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The return of Hong Kong has
filled more than 30 million residents in southwest China's
Chongqing municipality with great joy and excitement.
</P>
<P>
The city, approved to become a new municipality under the
direct administration of the central government, was immersed in
festivity as all the city from the main city area to the 600-km
Three Gorges reservoir zone to Qianjiang in the Wuling Mountainous
area were beautifully decked out. Rows of decorative lanterns were
lit to illuminate the city dotted with colorful banners and scrolls
everywhere.
</P>
<P>
Most attractive among the variety of activities celebrating
Hong Kong's return to the motherland was a "motorcycle parade"
sponsored by a local motorcycle manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
A caravan of 1,997 locally produced Jialing-brand motorcycles,
heralded by the national flag and the regional flag of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region and a big watchword board, was
advancing in neat lines through the city's major streets and
across the Yangtze and Jialing rivers.
</P>
<P>
Joyful and prolonged cheers were heard everywhere when the
motorcade passed by.
</P>
<P>
"I feel really very proud driving the motorcycle produced by
ourselves to participate in the parade to mark the historic event
of Hong Kong's return, and I also feel very proud of the
prosperity of our country and the development of our national
industry," said an official from the local Jialing Group Company.
</P>
<P>
In the Chaotianmen port zone where the Jialing River joins the
Yangtze, an orchestra and a singing team made up by 200 local port
workers sang songs to show their love for the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"How are you, Hong Kong; return, return." The audience burst into
exciting cheers again and again.
</P>
<P>
At midnight when the exciting moment came, scores of ships
anchoring along river banks sounded sirens to extend their
greetings to the more than 6 million Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
In the newly built People's Square, the main gathering place in
Chongqing to celebrate the return of Hong Kong, tens of thousands of
citizens from all walks of life sang and danced.
</P>
<P>
As the clock ticked closer to zero, the crowed cheered in
and shouted in chorus: Welcome Home, Hong Kong!
</P>
<P>
The gala party was brought to its climax when a colorful dragon
and carp-lantern dance rose amidst the deafening sound of the
beating of drums and gongs.
</P>
<P>
"At the very moment, the nation's grand dream of Hong Kong's
return has at last been materialized," said Li Yuejin, a young
Chongqing resident who during the past one year has traveled more
than 80,000 kilometers across the country to publicize the
significance of the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gala party ended with a chorus "My Motherland" by all the
people in the square. The song reverberated in the sky over this
hilly city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
