<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Rita Fan, President of Hong Kong PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- "The establishment of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) is for Hong Kong's smooth
transition, and what has been done by the PLC is also for the
smooth transition," PLC President Rita Fan said.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan became a member of the 60-strong provisional
legislature on December 21, 1996, and was elected the PLC
President at the body's first plenary meeting on January 25, 1997.
</P>
<P>
She had served on the Executive Council of the British Hong
Kong government in 1989-1992 and the Legislative Council in
1983-1992.
</P>
<P>
Born in Shanghai in 1945, Fan received education at Hong Kong's
St. Stephen's Girls' College before entering Hong Kong University.
</P>
<P>
She got Bachelor of Science (in Chemistry and Physics),
Certificate in Personnel Management and Master of Social Science
(in Psychology) from the university.
</P>
<P>
Fan is also a member of the Preparatory Committee for the
HKSAR, vice chairman of the Board of Convenors of the Association
for Celebration of Reunification of Hong Kong with China and vice
chairman of the Executive Committee of the association.
</P>
<P>
She is married with a daughter and a son. 
</P>
</TEXT>
