<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Leader's Treason Charges Dropped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- One of Sierra Leone's top prosecutors
today ensured that no further action would be taken in prosecuting
treason charges against junta leader Johnny Paul Koroma and
eight other soldiers, according to report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Solicitor General Pierre Boston, signed a nolle prosequi
document, declaring the state would proceed no further with the
charges against the accused, which relate to an alleged attempt to
overthrow the civilian government last October.
</P>
<P>
Koroma was jailed pending trial until he was sprung by soldiers on
May 25, when a coup brought him to power.
</P>
<P>
The document means treason charges against all nine soldiers,
including one woman, have been dropped, a state prosecutor was quoted
as saying.  
</P>
