<HEADLINE> Bell Striking To Celebrate HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- At 11:30 tonight, representatives
from various circles in China's eastern city of Nanjing gathered
at Jinghai Temple here and sounded a specially-crafted bell to
celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Lin Gang and Deng Yuan, descendants of the late Chinese
national heroes Lin Zexu and Deng Tingzhen, who led the Chinese
troops to resist British aggression in the Opium War, together
took the first strike at the bell.
</P>
<P>
"We have been waiting and striving for this moment for
generations, and now our ancestors will have no more regrets,"
said an emotional Lin Gang.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing is where the Treaty of Nanking was signed in 1842,
which ceded Hong Kong to Britain.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Yu Xiaodong, a bank clerk, proposed that an alarm
bell be made to remind people of this historical period. In
response, local residents donated more than 1 million yuan for the
bell.
</P>
<P>
The bell was struck 155 times to commemorate the 155-year
history of humiliation and people's struggle for reunification.
</P>
<P>
With people counting down the strikes in unison, Nanjing Mayor
Wang Hongmin took the last whack just as the clock reached the
zero hour of July 1. The sound echoed throughout the city,
declaring the end of the history of humiliation and the beginning
of a new era for Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
