<HEADLINE> Over 3,300 Ethiopian Projects Receive Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority announced today that 3,306 projects have been issued
with investment certificates over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar here, General Manager of the authority
Tadese Haile said out of the amount, 3,258 projects with a total
capital of 22 billion Birr (about 3.3 billion U.S.Dollars) are
domestic investments, while 48 projects with a total capital of
3.7 billion Birr (about 550 million U.S.Dollars) are foreign.
</P>
<P>
The general manager said that the investment code issued in
1992 and later revised in 1996 provides comprehensive packages of
incentives to both local and foreign investors in order to
encourage them to play a prominent role in the country's economic
development.
</P>
<P>
According to latest world investment directory issued here by
the United Nations conference on trade and development in May,
1997, foreign direct investment into Ethiopia has gone
considerable changes, in line with the political system in the
country. During the 1960 and up to the mid-1970s, Ethiopia
attracted substantial amounts of foreign direct investment.
</P>
<P>
However, between 1974 and 1991, all economic bodies in
Ethiopia were controlled by the military regime of junta, there
were no new foreign-direct-investment flows into ethiopia during
this period. the new government, which came into power in 1991,
tried to eliminate the inherited constrains on foreign direct
investment and to establish an enabling environment for foreign
investors. Foreign investors have begun to show interest in
Ethiopia since this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
