Albanian President Sali Berisha conceded Monday that his ruling
Democratic Party lost in the first round of elections on Sunday,
which the international polling monitors described as "adequate
and acceptable,"
</P>
<P>
The general elections in Albania came after several months of
civil conflict sparked by the collapse of pyramid investment
schemes in January. More than 1,500 people were killed in the
clashes.
</P>
<P>
Reppas said the further strengthening of relations between
Athens and Tirana would help protect the rights of the ethnic
Greek community in Albania. 
