<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Gala Celebration for Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The spectacular Beijing Worker's
Stadium was aglow with 200 floodlights and the patriotic fervor of
an audience of 80,000 when President Jiang Zemin spoke about the
return of Hong Kong today.
</P>
<P>
The stadium rocked with applause and cheering when Jiang told
the crowd, made up of people from all walks of life and ethnic
groups in China, "The more than six million Hong Kong compatriots
have now come back to the embrace of the great motherland."
</P>
<P>
"The vast land of China is a scene of jubilation and people
from all corners of the world are watching Hong Kong," Jiang
said. "The return of Hong Kong and the 100-year expectation of the
Chinese people, has finally come true."
</P>
<P>
Following the president's speech, a grand-scale performance was
presented by more than 18,000 singers, dancers, actresses and
actors. As a group of more than 1,000 children pranced to center
stage and began dancing, 10,000 balloons were released into the
night sky and the inscription "Celebrating the Return of Hong
Kong," written by Jiang, appeared on the stadium's backdrop.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese five-star national flag was moved onstage by
People's Liberation Army soldiers and solemnly raised as the
audience sang the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong celebrities also participated in the extravaganza,
Dressed in ethnic costumes, they joined hands with performers from
the inland and sang "Family Reunion" while 1,997 fireworks were
set off over the stadium.
</P>
<P>
The gathering was broadcast live by the China Central
Television to more than 100 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
