<HEADLINE> Macao Should Do Better After HK's Return: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Macao needs to do better for a smooth
handover of power in two and half years, a high-ranking Chinese
official said here today, following the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
made the remarks today at a reception for China's resumption of
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and the establishment of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The localization of senior and middle ranking civil service,
the localization of law and the use of Chinese as an official
language should pick up speed and have "breakthrough" within next
year, he told about 600 guests attending the reception.
</P>
<P>
He urged Macao residents to get united and work hard to
promote the Basic Law of Macao and to make preparations for the
handover in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The director said the cooperation between China and Portugal
need to be strengthened for the handling of transitional affairs
in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"China and Portugal have kept good cooperation since Macao
entered its transitional period," he said. "We hope the two sides
can constantly increase common ground and work effectively so that
a stable transition and smooth handover of power will be ensured."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return to the motherland is an important step in
China's reunification, and will serve as a model for Macao and
Taiwan, he commented.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong is the first stop in China's reunification cause in
accordance with the principle of 'one country, two systems,'" he
said. "Hong Kong's smooth return to the motherland will help a
smooth handover in Macao and the reunification of Taiwan with the
mainland." 
</P>
</TEXT>
