<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis, Sanchez Move into Last Eight in Wimbledon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When rain stopped play for the second time in mid-afternoon,
three-times champion Boris Becker looked to be on his way to
victory and held a 6-2, 6-2, 0-3 lead over Chile's clay-court
specialist Marcelo Rios.
</P>
<P>
Sandrine Testud, who ended the hopes of second-seed Monica
Seles 24 hours earlier, beat French Fed Cup teammate Nathalie
Tauziat 6-4, 5-7, 6-5.
</P>
<P>
Hingis scored a 6-1, 6-3 victory over Belgian Sabine Appelmans
and now plays either Maria Vento of Venezuela or 18-year-old
Denisa Chladkova of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario defeated French opponent Mary Pierce 6-1, 6-3
in less than an hour.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Greg Rusedski slammed down a barrage of 32 aces to
overwhelm Richey Reneberg of the United States 7-6 (7/2), 6-4, 7-6
(7/4) and reach a showdown with Frenchman Cedric Pioline for a
place in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Pioline put out Brett Steven of New Zealand 3-6, 6-3, 6-4, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Stich, who has curtailed his career because of persistent
shoulder problems, defeated Australian doubles specialist Mark
Woodforde 6-4, 6-7 (3/7), 6-3, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old German now plays either defending champion
Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands or Britain's 14th seed Tim
Henman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
