<HEADLINE> Angolan President Calls for UNITA'S Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President and Chairman of
the People's Movement for the Liberation of Angola currently in
power, Eduardo Dos Santos today calls for the cooperation of the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) with
the government in speeding up the implementation of the Lusaka
Peace Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos made the appeal at the opening ceremony of the
Second National Conference of the People's Movement for the
Liberation of Angola.
</P>
<P>
According to the president, the primary task now for the peace
process is the reestablishment of national administrations, the
realization of free trade and UNITA's dispersing of all armed
people who have not entered the concentration areas.
</P>
<P>
The delays in the peace process and clashes in the north and
north-east border areas should not discourage all parties
involved, nor would they change the general direction of the
peace process, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Second National Conference of the People's Movement is the
party's first national meeting since the multi-party elections in
September 1992. The conference will be concluded on July 4.
</P>
</TEXT>
