<HEADLINE> German Troops Start Mission to Assist Return of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A special unit of the German armed
forces has begun data-collecting operations in Bosnia to assist
the repatriation of Bosnian refugees living in Germany, the German
armed forces announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The unit of 40 soldiers who can speak local languages will be
deployed in southeastern Bosnia to collect information on towns
and villages where Bosnian refugees will be able to find a home
without fearing attacks. They are expected to supply the German
embassy in Sarajevo with their data.
</P>
<P>
According to German authorities, Some 45,000 Bosnian refugees
currently living in Germany are willing to return to southeastern
Bosnia. 
