<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Myanmar Gives Reception for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to Myanmar Chen
Baoliu hosted a grand reception here this evening to mark China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong today.
</P>
<P>
About 400 guests, including First Secretary of the Myanmar
State Law and Order Restoration Council Khin Nyunt, Second
Secretary Tin Oo, several government ministers, as well as foreign
diplomats, attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the reception, Khin Nyunt said that Myanmar,
along with many other countries which suffered the similar bitter
experiences of colonial scourges, as well as the people of the
whole world "warmly welcome the reunification."
</P>
<P>
Myanmar fully shared the jubilant sentiments of the Chinese
people, he said.
</P>
<P>
This successful reunification can be mainly attributed to the
concept of "one country, two systems" expounded by Deng Xiaoping,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Myanmar's confidence that "prosperity and
development of the HKSAR (Hong Kong Special Administrative Region)
will be further enhanced."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Chinese Consulate-General in Mandalay, the
second largest city of Myanmar, also gave a reception there to
mark the occasion.  
