<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Austria Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in Austria held
a grand reception here today to celebrate Hong Kong's return to
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Chinese Ambassador to Austria, Wang
Yanyi, said Hong Kong's return marked the end of Britain's more
than 150 years' colonial rule in Hong Kong, and wiped away a
national shame.
</P>
<P>
The resolution of the Hong Kong issue brought about by Deng
Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two systems" has set a model
for the ultimate resolution of the Macao and Taiwan issues, Wang
said.
</P>
<P>
Those invited to the party included President of the National
Council Heinz Fischer and former president Kurt Waldheim. 
