<HEADLINE> Leaders of Four Nations Hail HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of Myanmar, the Philippines,
Russia and Malaysia have sent messages of congratulations to
China, hailing Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of Myanmar's State Law and Order Restoration Council
(head of state), Than Shwe, said China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereign over Hong Kong is an event well worth
celebrating.
</P>
<P>
It would help promote the development of the Chinese economy,
and the principle of "one country, two systems" adopted by the
Chinese government to solve the Hong Kong issue would be carried
out smoothly and successfully there.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Fidel Ramos said China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong would contribute to the
stability and progress of Hong Kong, China's inland areas and the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin said: "I am confident that Hong
Kong will remain a prosperous financial and economic hub in Asia
and the world after the People's Republic of China resumes the
exercise of sovereignty over it."
</P>
<P>
"This will prove that Deng Xiaoping's concept of 'one country,
two systems' is viable. I hope Hong Kong will become another
active participant in Russia-China cooperations." he added.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Acting Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim said his country
welcomes the historical event marking the end of colonial rule
of more than 150 years in eastern Asia.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the traditional and friendly relations between
Malaysia and Hong Hong would continue to develop, making greater
contribution to the comprehensive strengthening of relations
between Malaysia and China as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
