<HEADLINE> Lebanese PM congratulates China on Hong Kong's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik
Hariri said today that the return of Hong Kong to China after
156 years of British rule is the logic of history.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua correspondent, the Lebanese Prime
Minister said, "the return of Hong Kong to China is an important
historic event".
</P>
<P>
Hariri expressed his congratulations to the Chinese leadership
and the Chinese people on the return of that dear part of Chinese
territory to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
He recalled his visits to China last year and his meetings with
Chinese leaders, saying he felt the economic renaissance achieved
by China during the visit. He said that he is confident of
China's ability to make maximum use of the return of that dear
part of its territory and the experience of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hariri said that some ill-willed people in the world are trying
to create problems between China and Britain or between Hong Kong
and the inland areas of China, but China is a great country which
is marching forward with confidence. 
</P>
