<HEADLINE> 80,000 People Meet to Celebrate HK's Return (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Eighty thousand people from various
walks of life in the Chinese capital got together this evening at
the Beijing Workers' Stadium to celebrate Hong Kong's return to
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the rally at the stadium, President Jiang Zemin said
that "Hong Kong has finally come back to the motherland, Macao
will come back soon, and a promising prospect of a complete
national reunification and all-round rejuvenation of the Chinese
nation is now in sight." Jiang is also the general secretary of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and Chairman
of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
The evening party was sponsored by the CPC Central Committee,
the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, the State
Council, the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) National Committee and the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
It began at 19:30 (Beijing Time) amid "Ode to the Motherland"
sung by 10,000 people to the accompaniment of music played by
1,000 instrumentalists. Some 5,000 middle school students formed
a pattern of the national emblem of the People's Republic of China
on the grandstand, drawing enthusiastic cheers from the crowds.
</P>
<P>
At 20:00, 99 salvos of fireworks were let off in the
stadium. Then, all rose to sing the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Communist Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao
Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren
were present.
</P>
<P>
Over the stadium was hung a gigantic streamer which read:
"Celebrate Hong Kong's Return and Make Concerted Efforts to Create
a Bright Future". And a slogan reading "Warmly Celebrate the 76th
Anniversary of the Founding of the Communist Party of China" was
displayed on a large electronic screen.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of People on the bleachers formed six Chinese
characters inscribed by Chinese President Jiang Zemin, which mean
"Celebrate Hong Kong's Return".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
