<HEADLINE> Arafat Arrives in Tunis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
President Yasser Arafat arrived here today on a previously
unannounced visit to Tunisia.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will brief Tunisian President Zine al-Abidine Ben Ali
on the outcome of his visit to France. The two leader will also
exchange views on ways and means to safeguard the peace process
from total collapse, according to reports released by the
Palestine News Agency (WAFA).
</P>
<P>
Arafat is accompanied by Hani Al Hassan, a member of the
central committee of the PLO mainstream Fateh movement, PNA
Minister of Local Government Saeb Erekat and Nabil Abu Rudaina,
press adviser to Arafat.
</P>
<P>
The PNA president paid a one-day visit to France Monday where
he met with French President Jacques Chirac and Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin to discuss the prospects of activating the stumbling
Middle East peace process.  
