<P>
On behalf of the Communist Party of China, the Central People's
Government and people of all ethnic groups throughout China, Jiang
extended warm congratulations on the return of Hong Kong and the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong marks an end to the 100-year national
humiliation of leaving Hong Kong under foreign occupation and has
opened a new era of common development of Hong Kong and the
inland areas of the motherland," Jiang Zemin said.
</P>
<P>
"It also symbolizes an important step in the great cause of
achieving national reunification and a new contribution of the
Chinese people to world peace, development and progress," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Comrade Deng Xiaoping made historic contribution
to the settlement of the Hong Kong question and the promotion of
the complete reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"We shall carry forward his legacy and work to ensure the
success of Hong Kong and that of our modernization program and
national reunification," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also paid a great tribute to Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai, Liu
Shaoqi, Zhu De and other proletarian revolutionaries of the older
generation who were founders of New China.
</P>
<P>
Through their hard struggle, the Chinese people overturned
feudalism, imperialism and bureaucrat-capitalism and opened a new
epoch of maintaining independence and building socialism, Jiang
said, adding that the Chinese nation will no longer allow itself
to be bullied, oppressed and exploited by others.
</P>
<P>
"Today, the Chinese people have made remarkable achievements in
their modernization endeavor," Jiang said. "As a result, China now
enjoys a higher international status in the world. It is against
this background and for this very reason that Hong Kong has come
back to China."
</P>
<P>
"We will unswervingly carry out the principles of 'one country,
two systems', 'Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong' and 'a high
degree of autonomy', and make sure that the current socioeconomic
system and way of life of Hong Kong remain unchanged and that the
laws now in force in Hong Kong remain basically unchanged," Jiang
Zemin said.
</P>
</TEXT>
