<HEADLINE> 80,000 People Meet to Celebrate HK's Return (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang's speech was interrupted by thunderous applause time and
again. At the end of his speech, 18,000 people presented a pageant
of songs and dances "Celebrate Hong Kong's Return", which was in
three parts describing China's recent history from national
humiliation to Hong Kong's return. The pageant was being
illustrated by various patterns formed by 5,000 people on the
grandstand.
</P>
<P>
During the 55-minute theatrical performance, Dr. Sun Yat-sen's
testament calling for abrogating unequal treaties was broadcast,
as well as the recordings of Mao Zedong's statement that "the
Chinese people have stood up" and Deng Xiaoping's remark about the
"one country, two systems" concept.
</P>
<P>
Well-known artists and performers from Hong Kong and the inland
areas joined in their presentations. Lion dances performed by 300
people from Hong Kong and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"My Chinese Heart" sung by the Hong Kong singer Cheung Ming-man
and "Nostalgia" played by the violinist Sheng Zhongguo expressed
the Chinese people's feelings about wiping out national
humiliation and celebrating national unity with Hong Kong's return
to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the rally, a 7,000-square-meter national flag
formed by people appeared in the stadium. While a presenter was
reciting Jiang Zemin's call for the reunification of the
motherland and national solidarity, a salvo of 1,997 guns was
fired. At the same time, fireworks were let off at six places
in Beijing's urban and suburban areas.
</P>
<P>
Also speaking at the rally were Wei Jianxing, secretary of the
Beijing Municipal Communist Party Committee; Fei Xiaotong, who
represented the non-Communist parties, the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce, and non-party figures; and Huang Qizao, who
represented the people's organizations.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys to China were invited to attend the great
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
