<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Chairman Pledges Faithful Execution of HKSAR Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), today hailed
the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) and pledged to implement to the letter the HKSAR Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR became an official entity as of midnight on June 30,
when China resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
after more than 150 years of British colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
At the plenary session of the 26th session of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress this afternoon,
Qiao announced the formation of the HKSAR Basic Law Committee of
the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Qiao expressed the hope that the Committee should perform its
duties well and make contributions to the faithful execution of
the Basic Law and the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The NPC HKSAR Basic Law Committee is made up 12 members, half
of whom come from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The session adopted a resolution on the additions and
deductions of the provisions of national laws listed in Appendix 3
of the HKSAR Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The session was presided over by NPC Vice-Chairman Tian Jiyun.
</P>
</TEXT>
