<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Approves National Laws for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature, today
approved a decision on national laws to be enacted in Hong Kong
after July 1.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision adopted by the 26th session of the
NPC Standing Committee, which opened on June 27, five national
laws are to be added and one deletion made from Annex 3 of the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The five laws to be added are: the National Flag Law of the
People's Republic of China (PRC); Resolutions on Consular
Privileges and Immunity in the PRC; the Law on the National Emblem
of the PRC; the Law on China's Territorial Waters and Adjoining
Areas; and the Garrison Law of the People's Liberation Army Troops
Stationed in the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The law to be deleted is the Order on the National Emblem of
the PRC Proclaimed by the Central People's Government,
Attached: Design of the national emblem, Notes of explanation and
Instructions for Use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
