<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Press Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The world press hailed Hong Kong's
return to China and expressed optimism about its future.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong under the principle of "one country,
two systems" is an unprecedented event, which shows the wisdom of
the late Chinese leader, Deng Xiaoping, said an editorial of the
leading Japanese newspaper, Asahi Shimbun.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is going to be more stable and prosperous after its
return to the motherland with Hong Kong and the inland areas of
China promoting the development of each other, said an editorial
of Malaysia's major Chinese language newspaper, Nanyang Siang Pan.
</P>
<P>
The resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong by
China is not only a happy event for China but also a major event
in Asia, said Nanyang Siang Pan.
</P>
<P>
The New Straits Times, the largest English language daily of
Malaysia, said in its editorial that this historic event marks a
new era for Hong Kong, and forecasts its bright future.
</P>
<P>
Times of India pointed out in its editorial that China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong righted a
wrong in history. It said that under the British colonial rule,
Hong Kong had no democracy at all.
</P>
<P>
Algeria's official daily El Moudjanid published an editorial,
calling the return of Hong Kong a great historic event for China
which shows the triumph of China in diplomacy and wisdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
