<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Rally to Celebrate HK's Return (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Today, the Chinese and British governments have held a
ceremony for the handover of Hong Kong, declaring the Chinese
Government's resumption of its exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong. The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of the
People's Republic of China has been formally established," Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
With the rising of the five-star red flag and the regional flag
of the SAR over Hong Kong, the over six million Hong Kong
compatriots have now come back to the embrace of the great
motherland, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The vast land of China is a scene of jubilation and people all
over the world are following this event closely. The return of
Hong Kong, the Chinese people's expectation over the past century,
has finally come true, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong marks an end to the 100-year national
humiliation of leaving Hong Kong under foreign occupation and has
opened a new era of common development of Hong Kong and the
inland areas of the motherland," Jiang Zemin said.
</P>
<P>
"It also symbolizes an important step in the great cause of
achieving national reunification and new contribution of the
Chinese people to world peace, development and progress," he said.
</P>
<P>
Time and again, Jiang's speech was interrupted by thunderous
applause. At the end of his speech, 18,000 people presented songs
and dances to celebrate Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Toward the end of the rally, a salvo of 1,997 guns was fired in
the stadium and fireworks were let off at six places in Beijing's
urban and suburban areas.
</P>
<P>
Also addressing the rally were Wei Jianxing, secretary of the
Beijing Municipal Communist Party Committee; Fei Xiaotong, a
representative of the non-Communist parties, the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, and non-party figures; and
Huang Qizao, who represented people's organizations.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys to China also attended the great event.
</P>
</TEXT>
