<HEADLINE> Former Afghan President Calls for Iran's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Former Afghan president and
leader of the Afghan National Liberation Front Sibghatullah
Mojaddedi today called for continuation of Iran's mediation to
put an end to the civil war in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that Mojaddedi, who
arrived here Monday afternoon for talks with Iranian officials,
made the remarks in his meeting with Iranian Foreign Minister Ali
Akbar Velayati.
</P>
<P>
Mojaddedi said his visit is aimed at making efforts to end the
crisis in Afghanistan, adding that Iran has always favored
cessation of war and restoration of peace and tranquility in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Velayati was quote as saying that the victories
and defeats in Afghanistan prove that a specific group cannot
rule Afghanistan and any foreign intervention will further
deteriorate the situation in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that a peaceful breakthrough must be found to
resolve the Afghan crisis, Velayati said that any efforts to
reach a long-term solution will be valuable.
</P>
<P>
"Preventing bloodshed and war will be a great service to the
Afghan nation," he said. 
</P>
