<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Donates "Life-Line Express" to Inland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- On behalf of people from all
walks of life in Hong Kong, Tung Chee-hwa, Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), today donated a
life-line express equipped with medical instruments to the inland
areas.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office
under the State Council, accepted the express.
</P>
<P>
The donation of the train on the first day of Hong Kong's
return to China is of great significance, said Nellie Fong
Kut-man, chairman of the Life-Line Express Executive Committee.
</P>
<P>
She added the express will help the poor and needy "to regain
health" in remote parts of the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The three-car express has two operation rooms, one consultation
room, one examination room, and other facilities.
</P>
<P>
The express will visit five selected remote areas each year, to
provide free medical service for cataract victims. Eight doctors
in Hong Kong are ready to take part in the work in the first year
of the express.
</P>
<P>
The express departed from Hung Hom Railway Station in Kowloon
this afternoon, for Fuyang in east China's Anhui province, its
first destination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
