<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Hails HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today sent a message of congratulations to China, hailing Hong
Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said: "I am confident that Hong Kong will remain a
prosperous financial and economic hub in Asia and the world after
the People's Republic of China resumes the exercise of sovereignty
over it."
</P>
<P>
"This will prove that Deng Xiaoping's concept of 'one country,
two systems' is viable. I hope Hong Kong will become another
active participant in Russia-China cooperations."
</P>
<P>
Russia upheld China's right to be reunified and stable. Russia
is ready to develop, with China, a 21st century-oriented strategic
coordination partnership established on equality and mutual trust,
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
