<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Rally Highlights National Unity and Patriotism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A number of Chinese officials
highlighted the importance of national unity and patriotism in
speeches to a crowd of some 80,000 Beijing people gathered at
Workers' Stadium this evening here in the Chinese capital to
celebrate Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The speakers urged their countrymen to unite more closely
around the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at its core in the period following the return of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They also vowed that the nation's officials will do their part
to step up the socialist modernization drive as well as the
reunification of the motherland, and revive the nation under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
"After the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, leading
officials at all levels in our city will strictly observe
the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administration Region and
further study and implement the central government's basic
principles and various policies regarding Hong Kong," said Wei
Jianxing, secretary of the Beijing Committee of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
He urged that exchanges and cooperation between Beijing and
Hong Kong be broadened, and that the nation work for the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In addition, educational programs designed to spread patriotism
among the general public should be continued, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fei Xiaotong, on behalf of non-Communist parties and persons
and the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, said that
China lost its national dignity in the period between the Opium
War in 1840 and the founding of the New China in 1949. To change
its destiny, China waged bold and time-honored struggles, he said.
</P>
<P>
The prerequisites for the return of Hong Kong were the
achievements made in the socialist construction as well as the
rise of China's international status, Fei said.
</P>
<P>
He also referred to the praiseworthy unity among different
ethnic groups and that of all patriotic organizations, which
provide the basic guarantee of the nation's development course.
</P>
<P>
Huang Qizao, speaking for various non-governmental
organizations, said that without the Chinese people's long-term
struggles, and without the leadership of the Chinese Communist
Party, China could not have achieved its independence or seen
development and prosperity, nor could Hong Kong have returned to
the embrace of the motherland, she added.
</P>
<P>
Huang noted that the return of Hong Kong demonstrates the
success of Deng Xiaoping's "one country, two systems" concept, and
is an important milestone in the process to reunify the nation.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the reunification of our great motherland as a
whole will unquestionably be achieved one day," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
