<HEADLINE> Mammoth Rally in Beijing Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A rally of people from all walks of
life in the Chinese capital to celebrate Hong Kong's return to the
motherland began this evening at the Beijing Workers' Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, who is also the general
secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee
and chairman of the Central Military Commission, is scheduled to
deliver an important speech to the 80,000 participants in the
rally.
</P>
<P>
The celebration began at 19:30 (Beijing Time) amid "Ode to the
Motherland" sung by 10,000 people to the accompaniment of music
played by 1,000 instrumentalists. Some 10,000 middle school
students formed a pattern of the national emblem of the People's
Republic of China on the grandstand, drawing thunderous cheers
from the crowds.
</P>
<P>
The rally is sponsored by the CPC Central Committee, the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, the State
Council, the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) National Committee and the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
At 20:00, 99 salvos of fireworks were let off in the
stadium. Then, all present stood up to sing the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Communist Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao
Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren
are present at the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Over the stadium is hung a gigantic streamer which
reads: "Celebrate Hong Kong's Return and Make Concerted Efforts to
Create a Bright Future". And the scoreboard displays a slogan
reading "Warmly Celebrate the 76th Anniversary of the Founding of
the Communist Party of China".
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, secretary of the Beijing Municipal Communist
Party Committee; Fei Xiaotong, who represents the non-Communist
parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, and
non-party figures; and Huang Qizao who represents the people's
organizations will also give speeches at the rally.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys to China have also been invited to attend the
great event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
