<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Press Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian press today published
editorials and commentaries hailing the return of Hong Kong to
China, terming Hong Kong's handover as a final nail in coffin of
the British colonialism.
</P>
<P>
Persian Daily Abrar's political commentary said "China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
symbolizes the end of the era of humiliation."
</P>
<P>
"It also heralds the beginning of a new period in history in
which the colonial powers have declined," the daily said.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that Hong Kong's return to China is not
merely the return of a piece of land, but also the return of
national self-confidence, power and prestige.
</P>
<P>
The English daily Tehran Times today welcomed the return of
Hong Kong to China, saying that the event marks the end of the
British colonialism in the world.
</P>
<P>
The British empire was built at the cost of pauperization and
underdevelopment of a large number of countries and territories
in the southern hemisphere, it noted.
</P>
<P>
"Whether it was spice trade from India, rubber and jute from
south and southeast Asia or oil from Middle East, Great Britain
exploited host countries either through direct colonization or
long-term contracts," said the editorial.
</P>
<P>
Almost until the end of World War II, it said, no colony dared
to defy British colonial rule for the answer of the colonial
rulers to the empty-handed freedom fighters came through barrels
of gun and cannon.
</P>
<P>
"The handover of Hong Kong to China on July 1 was the final
nail in the coffin of British colonial rule in southeast
Asia. This gives a message for third world countries,
neocolonialism which replaced old colonialism will not last long
and the message for neocolonialism is that sooner or later it has
to perish," it said.
</P>
<P>
The Persian daily Kar-o-Karegar's political commentary said "the
return of Hong Kong can be source of achievement of great
results for China. In the first analysis, the return of this
island would mean the end of national humiliation, and an
end to bitter memories of the past defeats, and an end to
the colonial rule over a part of the Chinese territory."
</P>
<P>
The handover would be a boost to the national pride and
patriotism in China, it said.
</P>
<P>
The daily said "This is something that Chinese leaders have
been seeking in order to elevate China's international stature."
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, this victory can herald the resolution
of the Taiwan problem in the future, it added.
</P>
<P>
After taking over Hong Kong from the British and Macao from the
Portuguese, China would only think about Taiwan. The daily said,
the Chinese leaders hope that with the success of the concept of
"One Country, Two Systems," they would eventually bring about a
reunification of Taiwan with the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
