<HEADLINE> Hingis Reaches Wimbledon Tennis Quarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Martina Hingis became the
first women's player to reach the Wimbledon tennis quarterfinals
Tuesday when she downed Belgium's Sabine Appelmans 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hingis needed just 66 minutes to complete the
victory - just before play was suspended on all courts by the
first rain in four days.
</P>
<P>
In the only other match completed before the rain break,
Indonesia's Yayuk Basuki beat Patricia Hy-Boulais 6-0, 7-6 (7-2)
to reach the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
It was the first rain since last Friday, when the second of two
straight washouts forced Wimbledon to schedule play on the middle
Sunday for only the second time in history.
</P>
<P>
Among featured matches Tuesday, defending champion Richard
Krajicek was scheduled to meet Britain's Tim Henman.
</P>
<P>
In women's play, No. 3 Jana Novotna was paired gainst No. 11
Mary Joe Fernandez and No. 8 Arantxa Sanchez Vicario against No. 9
Mary Pierce.
</P>
<P>
Two three-time men's champions, Pete Sampras and Boris Becker,
are just one round away from the match everyone has been looking
forward to. Sampras was due to face No.16 Petr Korda with Becker
up against No. 9 Marcelo Rios. 
</P>
</TEXT>
