<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Opens Commissioner Office in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Office of Commissioner of the
Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) was inaugurated here today.
</P>
<P>
At the zero hour today, a five-star red flag, China's national
flag, was hoisted in front of the building of the commissioner
office.
</P>
<P>
The office will deal with relevant foreign affairs concerning
the HKSAR on behalf of the Central People's Government and will
serve as a channel through which the HKSAR government communicates
the central government over such affairs. Its establishment is an
important symbol of China's resumption of exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, Chief
Executive of the HKSAR Tung Chee Hwa and Commissioner of the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs in the HKSAR Ma Yuzhen attended the
inaugural ceremony held this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Extending warm congratulations on the inauguration of the
office on behalf of the Central People's Government, Qian said
that the resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
by the Chinese government is a great historical event for the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The event has filled the heart of every Chinese at home and
abroad with exultation and pride, as well as confidence in Hong
Kong's bright future, he added.
</P>
<P>
"To maintain the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong is the
strong desire of the Hong Kong compatriots, which is also shared
by their 1.2 billion fellow countrymen in the inland areas," he
said, adding that the Central People's Government would
unswervingly implement the policies of "one country, two systems",
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of
autonomy.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law of the HKSAR, he said, the Central
People's Government is responsible for the foreign affairs
concerning the HKSAR, while the HKSAR is granted the authority to
handle relevant external affairs on its own in accordance with the
law.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the wish that the Office of the Foreign Ministry
Commissioner in the HKSAR would maintain close contacts and
cooperation with the HKSAR government and make positive
contributions to safeguarding state sovereignty and interests,
protecting the legitimate rights and interests of the Hong Kong
compatriots, and promoting prosperity and stability in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung also congratulated on the establishment of
the Foreign Ministry's Commissioner Office in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that the establishment of the HKSAR marked a new era
for Hong Kong's development. He pledged that the SAR government
would spare no efforts to provide support and cooperation for the
work of the Foreign Ministry's Commissioner office.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner Ma said that his office would strictly abide by
the HKSAR Basic Law and would, under the leadership of the central
government and with assistance and cooperation of the SAR
government and the Hong Kong people, make every effort to complete
its mission.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed sincere gratitude to Hong Kong tycoon Li
Ka-shing, whose Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd. was involved in the
design and construction of the building of the office.
</P>
<P>
Located on the Hong Kong Island, the 20-floor building of the
Foreign Ministry's Commissioner Office in the HKSAR has a total
construction space of about 25,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Attending the inaugural ceremony were more than 400 people,
including foreign consuls-general in Hong Kong, principal
officials of the HKSAR government and noted local figures.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
