<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IOC President Samarach Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- International Olympic Committee
President Juan Antonio Samaranch arrived here Tuesday afternoon
for a brief visit of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"Samaranch is here to promote the Chinese National Exhibition
of Sports Arts which is to open in Shanghai during the Chinese
Eighth National Games in October this year," said Tu Mingde, an
official with the Chinese Olympic Committee.
</P>
<P>
The IOC President attended ceremonies for the Hong Kong
handover and the inauguration of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region government around midnight Monday.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch is scheduled to fly back to Hong Kong late Wednesday
to attend Thursday's Reunification Cup soccer match between an
all-star team of the International Football Federation (FIFA) and
their counterpart from the Asian Football Confederation (AFC).
</P>
</TEXT>
