<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Grand Reception Hails Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng and other Chinese
leaders turned out to join some 4,000 people here today at a grand
reception celebrating the return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng delivered an important speech at the reception
sponsored by the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The Banquet Hall on the second floor of the 38-year-old Great
Hall of the People, where the reception took place, was decorated
with a huge color picture showing Hong Kong's panorama flanked by
red flags, the emblem of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, red lanterns and colorful bunting, highlighting the return
of Hong Kong under the "one country, two systems" principle.
</P>
<P>
Other Chinese leaders including Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu
Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren attended the
reception.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech, Premier Li Peng said: "We are celebrating
not only the advent of a new era for Hong Kong and a major victory
for the great cause of China's peaceful reunification, but also a
great triumph for justice and progress of mankind.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong, which has gone through countless vicissitudes, has
finally returned to the embrace of the great motherland." Today,
as a grand festival for the Chinese nation, will go down in
history, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li emphasized that a democratic system that is consistent with
the provisions of the Basic Law and suits Hong Kong's reality will
surely develop in order and step by step in Hong Kong and the Hong
Kong compatriots will surely enjoy extensive rights and freedoms
beyond what existed during the colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
With the return of Hong Kong, the compatriots there have become
the real masters of the land, he said, adding that "they are fully
capable of creating an even better future by giving full play to
their wisdom and talent."
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that Hong Kong's return represents an important
milestone for the complete reunification of the motherland, and he
said he believes that the scientific formula of "one country, two
systems" initiated by Deng Xiaoping will work in Hong Kong and
Macao, and it should also work for Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Present at the reception were Communist Party and government
leaders, officials and ministers of relevant departments directly
under the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the State
Council, leaders of the non-Communist parties and the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, and non-party figures as well
as representatives from various non-governmental organizations and
the 56 ethnic groups in China.
</P>
<P>
Distinguished foreign guests now visiting the Chinese capital,
representatives of the United Nations agencies and international
organizations in Beijing, and diplomatic envoys here were also
present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
