<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Claims 14 Lives in Northern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed when the
minibus carrying them and a trailer collided on the Shahroud-Azad
Shahr route in northern Iran Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the accident
which took place 65 kilometers north of Shahroud, Semnan
province, also left 13 injured.
</P>
<P>
The trailer involved in the accident was heading for
Turkey. Hospital sources said that two of the people in the
trailer were wounded, one of whom was rushed to Tehran for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
Highway police are investigating the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
