<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claim 70,000 Lives Annually in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Road accidents claim over 70,000
lives every year in India, the highest in the world, said Dr. A.K.
Gupta, director of the Central Road Research Institute (CRRI),
here today.
</P>
<P>
New Delhi, capital of India, has accounted for nearly one
fourth of the fatalities in the country's 23 metropolitan cities.
More than 15 percent of fatalities in the country occur in 23
metropolitan cities.
</P>
<P>
"Increase in number of vehicles and lack of proper public
transport policy has lead to anarchy on the roads," he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
