<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grand Party Celebrates Birth of HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand cocktail party was held
here this afternoon to celebrate the establishment of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Chinese central government, Vice-premier Qian
Qichen extended congratulations to the HKSAR Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa, the HKSAR government and the six million Hong Kong
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
"The destiny of Hong Kong is closely related with that of the
motherland," Qian said. He voiced the belief that with a
long-cherished tradition of loving both the country and Hong Kong,
Hong Kong people would make greater contributions to the
development and prosperity of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He proposed a toast to the prosperity and stability of the
HKSAR and happy life for all the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa said in his toast that "the
establishment of the HKSAR represents a fresh beginning of Hong
Kong's history, and a new milestone in the great cause of
reunifying the motherland and building up the nation."
</P>
<P>
"We have the confidence and ability for building an even better
Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 local and overseas guests attended the grand
celebration party held at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center Extension.  
</P>
</TEXT>
