<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Example in Resolving HK Issue Peacefully: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Minister of Information
and Communications Jhala Nath Khanal said today that China has set
an example for settling disputes peacefully between countries
through resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong by
peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on the peaceful handover of Hong Kong to
China, Khanal said that the principle of "one country, two
systems", which was adopted to handle the Hong Kong issue, will
also provide other countries with experience in resolving the
problem of unification.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the CPN-UML, the Nepali government and the people,
Khanal, who is also member of the standing committee of the
Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxist Leninist, CPN-UML),
felicitated the Communist Party of China, the Chinese government,
the leadership and the people on the resumption of exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong from July 1.
</P>
<P>
Nepali former ambassador to China Tulsi Lal Amatya and some 40
others attended the seminar, which was jointly organized by the
National Council of CRI (China Radio International) Listeners
Clubs-Nepal and the Friendship Club Nepal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
