<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Diversion Canal Ready for Navigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A flotilla of boats sailed for the
first time Monday through the diversion canal which has been built
to allow navigation to continue on the Yangtze River as work on
the coffer dam, part of the Three Gorges Project, nears completion.
</P>
<P>
The 3.5-km-long canal, 350 meters in width at the bottom and 58
meters deep, is both wider and deeper than the Suez and Panama
canals, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The man-made canal, into which water from the river has been
diverted, will also be used to discharge floods when necessary.
</P>
<P>
Dredging of the canal floor is continuing to provide a better
possible passage for vessels.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
