<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM Leaves for Bahrain on Official Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 1 (Xinhua) - Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul-Salam
Majali left here for Bahrain this morning for a three-day official
visit in a bid to promote bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Majali is expected to meet Bahraini leaders
and other senior officials on bilateral relations and the latest
developments of regional issues, including the Middle East peace
process, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was accompanied by the Minister of Energy
and Mineral Resources Mohammad Saleh Hourani.
</P>
<P>
Early last month, Bahrain conducted a five-day industrial
exhibition in Amman and later signed a 3.5-million-Jordanian dinar
(about 5 million U.S. dollars) contract with Jordan to supply the
kingdom with overhead cables for a 400-kilovolt power linkage
between Jordan and Syria.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between Jordan and Bahrain last year reached
34.4 million dinars (about 49 million dollars), with Jordan's
export accounting two-fifths of it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
