<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in dull
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by 6.67 points to close at 1,981.28 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 80.27 million units, valued
at 191.07 million Singapore dollars (about 133.62 million US
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 175 to 89, while 355
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Recently listed Tianjin Zhong Xin was again the most actively
traded stock as it registered a turnover of 13.35 million units.
It was followed by Wing Tai which had 4.52 million shares traded.
Wing RCPS was next with four million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
NBT topped the gainers' list as it rose by 70 cents to finish
at 22.4 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign and Samanda Holdings increased by 40 cents each to end at
18.4 and 13.4 Singapore dollars respectively. GE Life and OUE
gained 30 cents each to close at 16 and 6.9 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, RHB Cap was the biggest loser as it declined
by 2.7 dollars to end at 1.7 Singapore dollars. Malaya Banking 200
fell by 1.2 dollars to close at 14.3 Singapore dollars, while
Creative 50 finished 30 cents lower at 24.3 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
