<HEADLINE> Beijing Grand Reception Marks Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1, (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese leaders have turned
out at a reception to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland today, a grand event which is now going on in the Great
Hall of the People here.
</P>
<P>
The leaders present include Premier Li Peng, chairman Qiao Shi
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, and
others.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng is addressing the reception attended by 4,000 people,
which was sponsored by the State Council, at press time.
</P>
<P>
Also present are officials and ministers of relevant
departments directly under the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee and the State Council, leaders of the non-Communist
parties and the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, and
non-party figures as well as representatives from various people's
organizations and the 56 ethnic groups in China.
</P>
<P>
Distinguished foreign guests now visiting the Chinese capital,
representatives of the United Nations agencies and international
organizations in Beijing, and diplomatic envoys here are also
present on the occasion.  
</P>
