<HEADLINE> Legitimate Interests of All Countries in HK to Be Protected: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that the legitimate interests of all countries in Hong Kong
will be protected by law.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a reception in celebration of the return of Hong
Kong, Li emphasized that a prosperous and stable Hong Kong serves
not only the interests of China but also those of other countries
in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong will continue to play a unique role in the
Asia-Pacific and global economy by remaining a separate customs
territory, free port and international financial, trade and
shipping center.
</P>
<P>
"As Hong Kong will maintain and improve its sound investment
environment already in place, we believe, all personages with
vision from the business community can see the bright prospect for
economic growth in Hong Kong and will increase their economic and
trade exchanges with it," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"The legitimate interests of all countries of the world in Hong
Kong will be protected by law", he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Li said Hong Kong's return to the motherland has injected fresh
vitality into its economy, and Hong Kong is blessed with
exceptional advantages for its economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The sustained, rapid and sound development of national economy
in the inland areas as a result of the reform and opening policy
has provided the economy of Hong Kong with strong support, he
pointed out, adding that an enhanced role of Hong Kong as a bridge
and linkage between the economy of the inland areas and the
international economy will facilitate the modernization drive of
the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
