<HEADLINE> Uganda Plans for New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has embarked on a project
to establish a development strategy for the next 25 years,
reported the local daily "The New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
The strategy, code-named Uganda Vision 2025 was funded by the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP), the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is the 16th country in Africa to embark on such a
venture.
</P>
<P>
Sam Kuteesa, state minister for planning and economic
development was quoted as saying, "we in Uganda are fortunate to
be among a number of African countries currently involved in the
process of preparing national long-term perspective studies with
a view to formulating its long-term vision for national
development."
</P>
<P>
Uganda Vision 2025 will be formulated by the Uganda National
Core Team. The UNDP had already earmarked up to 1.5 million U.S.
Dollars for the exercise.
</P>
<P>
In Uganda, human development-based initiatives are a recent
phenomenon. Uganda's human development index of 0.328 registered
in 1994 ranked it the 150th out of 175 countries in the global
ranking of human development. Among 44 sub-Sahara African
countries, Uganda was ranked the 29th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
