<HEADLINE> Central Government Presents Valuable Gift Sculpture to HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A giant sculpture, a gift
presented to the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) by
the Central People's Government, was erected today by Victoria
Harbor at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The sculpture, called "Ever-Blooming Bauhinia", was presented
to the Hong Kong SAR, which was founded early this morning, by
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen on behalf of the Central People's
Government.
</P>
<P>
A simple yet solemn gift-presentation ceremony was held at the
center at noon today. Amid the strains played by a band of the
Hong Kong police, Qian presented to Tung Chee Hwa, the Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong SAR, the certificate of the gift from
the Central People's Government of the People's Republic China.
</P>
<P>
The glittering bauhinia, a flower to represent the Hong Kong
SAR, brings profound feelings and best wishes of the Central
People's Government for the Hong Kong SAR, a lady attending the
ceremony said.
</P>
<P>
The work of art, which weighs 70 tons and is six meters long,
wide and high respectively, is made of bronze and coated with gold
foils. It has a cylinder-shaped base with a squared bottom.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
directly under the Central Government in China's interior areas
also presented gifts to the Hong Kong SAR to honor its return to
the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
