<HEADLINE> Zambian Copper Mines Sold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Luanshya Division of the
Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM) has been sold to the
Binani Group during the privatization process of the state-owned
copper conglomerate ZCCM.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by ZCCM Executive Chairman Luke Mwanashiku
last night said the Binani Group has been selected as the winning
bidder for the ZCCM's Luanshya and Baluba Mining and
Metallurgical Complex excluding the precious metals plant.
</P>
<P>
Binani is an international diversified group of companies
engaged in mining, metal trading and manufacturing. It has been
actively involved in the marketing of Zambia's metals since 1955.
</P>
<P>
The Luanshya Division is one of the six major mines to be
privatized by the ZCCM. The Luanshya and Baluba mines produced
48,245 tons of copper and 1,216 tons of cobalt during the last
financial year ending March 31 this year. 
</P>
