<HEADLINE> Celebration for HKSAR Establishment Held (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- People from all walks of life
gathered here today in the Extension to the Hong Kong Convention
and Exhibition Center (HKCEC) to celebrate the founding of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, who is also general secretary of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, delivered an
important speech at the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, who was sworn in early today as chief executive
of the HKSAR, also spoke at the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Like elsewhere in the rest of China, Hong Kong is charged with
a festive atmosphere, with jubilant crowds cheering the birth of
the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
In a hall inside the Extension, the venue of the celebration,
hang the five-star national flag of the People's Republic of China
and the regional flag of the Hong Kong SAR featuring a bauhinia, a
flower representing Hong Kong. More than 4,000 representative from
all walks of life in Hong Kong, guests from the interior areas of
China and from abroad attended the celebration.
</P>
<P>
 When Jiang Zemin and other Chinese leaders, accompanied by Mr
Tung Chee Hwa, entered the hall at 10 am, the hall burst with
applause. This was the first time a Chinese head of state joined
Hong Kong people in a joyous celebration.
</P>
<P>
The celebration began amid the national anthem of the People's
Republic of China. Jiang Zemin delivered a speech on behalf the
central government and people of all nationalities, extending his
congratulations on Hong Kong's return to the motherland and the
founding of the HKSAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
