<HEADLINE> Celebration for HKSAR Establishment Held (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said Hong Kong's return to the motherland is a shining
page in the annals of the Chinese nation. From now on, he said,
Hong Kong compatriots will truly become masters here and a new
leaf will be turned in the annals of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"We cherish dearly and with great admiration the memory of Mr.
Deng Xiaoping, who passed away not long ago," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"He initiated, with exceptional wisdom and great statesmanship,
the creative vision of 'one country, two systems,' charting the
correct course for us to resolve the Hong Kong question through
diplomatic negotiations and to maintain the long-term prosperity
and stability of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president reaffirmed that the policies of "one
country, two systems," "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and
a high degree of autonomy will remain unchanged for 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also extended his congratulations to Mr. Tung Chee-hwa on
his assumption of office. "We have full confidence in the HKSAR
government under his leadership and will give it full support," he
said.
</P>
<P>
In the final analysis, he said, Hong Kong's success today is
the work of Hong Kong compatriots. Hong Kong compatriots will
certainly carry forward this valuable spirit and bring about a
better future for Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Hong Kong's success today is inseparable from
China's development and support from people in interior areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that, with the continuous advance of China's
modernization drive, Hong Kong's economic link with the interior
areas will become even closer, that its role as a bridge will be
increasingly enhanced, and that this in turn will give a stronger
impetus to Hong Kong's economic growth.
</P>
</TEXT>
