<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
recovered some losses of morning trading today in heavy trading
volume, following Monday's 2.4 percent surge.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 11 points lower at 2,491 with a turnover
of over 93 million NZ dollars (63 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
A rebound in Telecom shares pulled the market index off its
lows in the morning. The company's shares rose 5 cents to 755
cents. But Carter Holt Harvey lost 12c of Monday's 13c gain to
close at 370c.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand picked up 6c to 314c. Lion
Nathan edged up 1c to 374c and Fletcher Energy jumped 11c to 457c.
But Fletcher Paper fell 8c to 349c and Brierley Investment eased
1c to 143c.
</P>
<P>
There were 48 rises and 52 falls.  
