<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Agricultural Loans to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Manila-based Asian Development
Bank (ADB) today approved a 63.8 million US dollars loan to
Indonesia to help the country accelerate the transfer of
agricultural technologies to lower-income rural communities.
</P>
<P>
The bank said in a news release that farm incomes will be
increased and agricultural productivity will be improved in
Indonesia under the loan project.
</P>
<P>
The loan is also expected to encourage agribusiness, boost
exports, reduce urban-rural income disparities, promote balanced
regional growth, diversify agricultural production, address
changes in food demands and conserve natural resources, the ADB
said.
</P>
<P>
The loan has a maturity of 25 years, including a grace period
of seven years, at an interest rate determined in accordance with
the bank's pool-based variable lending rate for US dollar loans,
and an annual commitment fee of 0.75 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
