<HEADLINE> Miami Heat to Play Israeli Champion in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Miami Heat of the National
Basketball Association will play their first overseas game when
they take on Israel's Maccabi Tel Aviv in 1998, the NBA said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Heat will play the perennial Israeli champions on October
12, 1998. Miami finished a best of 61-21 in the 1996-97 regular
season and a 2-4 losser to the final NBA Champions Chicago Bulls
in the Eastern Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
Maccabi Tel Aviv has won the championship of Israel 26 times
in the last 27 years.
</P>
<P>
Maccabi Tel Aviv features former Connecticut collegiate stars
Nadav Henefeld and Doron Sheffer and Randy White, a former NBAer
of the Dallas Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
"Maccabi Tel Aviv has been one of the most successful clubs in
Europe during the past 25 years," NBA Commissioner David Stern
said. "This preseason game will offer fans in Israel a chance to
see their current champion against one of the top teams in the
NBA." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
