<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Newspapers Hail Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Newspapers here today hailed the
return of Hong Kong to China, saying the year 1997 is of great
significance in Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
All the newspapers here in Indonesian or English issued stories
on the first page on the ceremony marking the handover of Hong
Kong to China which took place at midnight on June 30 in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
In its editorial, "the Jakarta Post" says, "the sun has finally
set for the once great British empire with today's handover of
Hong Kong to China."
</P>
<P>
"But for the territory, and the rest of Asia, the sun will
shine even brighter," it notes.
</P>
<P>
The editorial points out that Hong Kong had been one of the few
last vestiges of European colonialism, which for most of Asia, is
a dark era in its history.
</P>
<P>
Any form of colonialism is deplorable and must, as a matter of
principle, be eliminated from the face of the earth, it adds.
</P>
<P>
On Hong Kong's future, the paper says most of the fears about
Hong Kong's future under Chinese rule are overplayed. Beijing has
assured it will maintain the current economic system in Hong Kong,
and it knows that it is in its own interests to do so.
</P>
<P>
"The Indonesian observer" in its editorial says, objectively
speaking, Hong Kong has the clout, experience and knowhow to
retain its position as one of the busiest business center in the
world.
</P>
<P>
"It is the goose that lays the golden egg, and China is wise
enough to keep it that way," it stresses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local press also reported the activities of
Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas in Hong Kong. The minister
is in Hong Kong as the Chinese government's guest to attend the
ceremony marking the handover of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with Hong Kong's chief executive Tung Chee Hwa on
Monday, Alatas, on behalf of the Indonesian government, people and
President Soeharto, congratulated China in connection with Hong
Kong's handover.
</P>
<P>
Alatas hoped the relations between Hong Kong and Indonesia can
be continued in the future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
