<HEADLINE> Senior Cuban Official Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Second secretary of the Cuban
Communist Party Central Committee and First vice-president of the
Council of State, Raul Castro, today hailed the return of Hong
Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
"This is a great and exciting historic moment," Castro told
Xinhua after watching the handover ceremony televised live in the
Chinese Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong is a matter of great importance not
only to China, but also to the rest of the mankind," Castro said.
</P>
<P>
Raul Castro, who was also minister of revolutionary armed
forces, expressed congratulations to China on behalf of Cuban
leader Fidel Castro.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong is the realization of the "one country,
two systems" concept, Castro said.
</P>
<P>
Other senior officials, including vice-president of the Council
of State and executive secretary of the Council of Ministers
Carlis Rage, President of the National Assembly of People's Power
Ricardo Alarcon and Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, were with
Castro in the Chinese Embassy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
