<HEADLINE> Consuls-general Urged to Promote Thailand's Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's honorary consuls-general
from over 50 countries have been urged to help promote the
kingdom's image, trade and tourism industry, and its suitability
for foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
About 90 foreign dignitaries gathered in a Bangkok hotel on
Monday for the five-day inaugural conference of the country's
honorary consuls-general.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh
called on the participants to help return the country to the path
of vigorous economic growth by attracting more foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Thailand faces a slowdown after a period of being an
"unstoppable Asian tiger cub destined to join the ranks of the
world's leading economies," Chavalit said.
</P>
<P>
He assured that Thailand's economic fundamentals are still
sound and that the government is introducing reforms which will
put the country back on the path of continued growth.
</P>
<P>
He said consuls-general are in an ideal position to steer
potential investors in the right direction by giving them the
facts and figures on Thailand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
