<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves Hong Kong for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
left here for Beijing by special plane shortly after 1:00 p.m.
today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier Qian Qichen and Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa were
at the airport to see him off.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang flew into here Monday afternoon for the Hong
Kong handover ceremony and the ceremony marking the establishment
of the HKSAR and the swearing-in of the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
He also met with Prince Charles, British heir-to-the-throne,
and British Prime Minister Tony Blair during his stay in Hong
Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
