<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese in Portugal Celebrate HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Overseas Chinese in Portugal held a
reception here today to mark the return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
Choi Manhin, president of the Portuguese-Chinese Association of
Industry and Commerce, said at the reception that Hong Kong's
return to the embrace of the motherland wiped out more than 150
years of national disgrace and ushered in a splendid future for
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
With Hong Kong's return, a big stride has been made in the
peaceful unification of China, which will be conducive to the
economic development not only in China, but also the Asian and
Pacific region and the world at large, Choi said.
</P>
<P>
At the time of the celebration, Choi said, the overseas Chinese
deeply cherished the memory of Mr. Deng Xiaoping, who put forward
the great concept of "one country, two systems," and the
principles of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high
degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
These concept and principles have provided fundamental
guarantees for Hong Kong's smooth transition and long time
stability and prosperity there. "We are confident that Hong
Kong's future will be more splendid," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Nuno Melo Egydio, president of the Portuguese-Chinese League of
Multi-Century Friendship and former governor of Macau, and other
friends in Portugal attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Overseas Chinese in Portugal held a rally
here also today, marking Hong Kong's return to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
