<HEADLINE> Chinese Consulate General Celebrates Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Consulate General in
New York held a grand reception for some 300 guests today to mark
Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
The guests came from the consulate generals of other countries,
New York city administration, big corporations and major local
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
Among them were the Chief of the Hong Kong Economic &AMP; Trade
Office Xu Junping, China's Permanent Representative to the Untied
Nations Qin Huasun and Deputy Permanent Representative Wang
Xuexian.
</P>
<P>
Consul General Qiu Shengyun hailed the official return of Hong
Kong to the motherland, which took place a few hours previously.
</P>
<P>
"This is one of the most important events in modern history,"
he said, "It marks the end of British colonial rule in Hong Kong
and opens a new era for Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
He believed the Chinese central government and the government
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region will work together
with all other countries and regions to ensure an even more
splendid future for Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
