<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Wins Manikganj By-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) candidate Abdul Wahab Khan won the
Manikganj-3 seat in the by-election held Monday, according to
unofficial results published here today.
</P>
<P>
Khan secured 59,374 votes while his nearest rival, ruling Awami
(people's) League's candidate Abdul Malek, polled 52,974, said the
Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
The parliament seat fell vacant with the death of BNP lawmaker
Nizamuddin Khan on March this year.
</P>
<P>
Voting in the keenly contested Manikganj by-election took place
peacefully amid tight security, said Deputy Commissioner of
Manikganj Abdur Razzauque, adding that the turnout was 75.69
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
