<HEADLINE> URGENT: Central Government, Provinces, Autonomous Regions and Municipalities Present Gifts to HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A list of gifts given to the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region by the
Central Government and the 31 provinces, autonomous regions and
centrally-administered municipalities in China's inland areas was
announced here today at a grand celebration party marking the
establishment of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The gift from the Central Government is a giant sculpture
called "Ever-Blooming Bauhinia." The bauhinia is a flower
representing the Hong Kong SAR.
The work of art has a bronze base, and the bauhinia, in full
bloom, is coated with gold.
The sculpture weighs 70 tons and will be erected by the Victoria
Harbor, symbolizing Hong Kong's eternal prosperity in the embrace
of the motherland. 
