<HEADLINE> Czech Media Hail HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Czech media today gave
extensive coverage of Hong Kong's return to China at midnight
tonight, hailing the end of the "colonial era" and forecasting
Hong Kong's future prosperity.
</P>
<P>
One newspaper called The People said in its editorial that
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over the island
marks "the end of Hong Kong's colonialist era."
</P>
<P>
It said China finally "won the Opium War," which broke out in
1840 between China's Qing Dynasty government and Britain, spelling
the beginning of more than 150 years of British colonial rule over
 Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Another newspaper, Rights, reported that most Hong Kong people
are confident of Hong Kong's future, as they believe that China
will keep its promise of "One Country, Two Systems", which ensures
Hong Kong a high degree of autonomy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
