<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador Hosts Reception for Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China's ambassador to Poland Chen
Shize today hosted a reception for more than 200 Polish friends
and Chinese living in the country to celebrate Hong Kong's return
to China.
</P>
<P>
The Polish Minister of Justice and other distinguished Poles
attended the reception. They hailed Hong Kong's peaceful return to
its motherland and spoke highly of the "one country, two systems"
principle advocated by the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Under the formula, China will keep the international financial
and trade center unchanged over the next 50 years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese embassy here organized a series of activities to
inform Polish people about Hong Kong's history and the great
significance of its return on July 1, when China resumes the
exercise of sovereignty over the region following 156 years of
British colonial rule. 
</P>
