<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Return Marks New Chapter in Hong Kong History, Jiang Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that the Hong Kong compatriots will truly become masters of
the region as it has now returned to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, made the remarks at the celebration for the
establishment of the Hong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
"Since ancient times, our ancestors have lived and labored on
this land generation after generation. From the Qin Dynasty to
Emperor Daoguang's Reign of the Qing Dynasty, China exercised
jurisdiction and sovereignty over Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
In mid-19th century, however, after launching two Opium Wars,
Britain forced the corrupt and incompetent Qing Government to sign
the Treaty of Nanking of 1842 and the Convention of Peking of
1860.
</P>
<P>
And in 1898, Britain again coerced the Qing Government into
signing the Convention of the Extension of Hong Kong, thus
occupying the entire Hong Kong region.
</P>
<P>
Despite the prolonged separation, Jiang noted, the
flesh-and-blood bond between the people on the mainland and Hong
Kong compatriots had never severed, nor had their shared sentiment
for the well-being of the nation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese people have never recognized the
unequal treaties imposed on them, never forgotten the humiliating
state of Hong Kong under occupation and never stopped their
indomitable struggle for state sovereignty and national
emancipation.
</P>
<P>
"The rise of the first Five-Star Red Flag at Tiananmen Square
(in Beijing) showed the world that China had achieved national
independence and liberation and embarked on a road to socialism,"
and thanks to reform and opening-up, "a rejuvenated Chinese nation
has taken on a completely new look, and its international stature
has been greatly enhanced," Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
It is under these conditions and against this historical
background that Hong Kong has finally returned to the motherland,
he said.
</P>
<P>
In these days of national jubilation for Hong Kong's return,
the Chinese people cherish with great admiration the memory of the
late Chinese leader, Mr Deng Xiaoping, he said.
</P>
<P>
Deng initiated, with exceptional wisdom and great
statesmanship, the creative concept of "one country, two systems,"
charting the correct course to resolve the Hong Kong question
through diplomatic negotiations and to maintain long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, the Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang elaborated the policies of "one country, two systems,"
"Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong" and "a high degree of
autonomy."
</P>
<P>
These policies have been formulated by the Central People's
Government after careful consideration of the need to safeguard
both the immediate interests of the Hong Kong compatriots and the
fundamental interests of the Chinese nation, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Adherence to these policies serves Hong Kong, serves the
entire nation and serves the world as well. Therefore, there is no
reason whatsoever to change them," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He added that these policies, which have become one of China's
long-term basic principles, will remain unchanged for 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also extended sincere congratulations to Tung Chee Hwa,
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Government, who has been sworn in earlier today. He expressed
full confidence in the Hong Kong SAR Government under his
leadership and pledged full support to it.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region shall be observed not only in Hong Kong, but
also by all the departments of the Central Government as well as
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under
the Central Government, he noted.
</P>
<P>
No central department or locality may or will be allowed to
interfere in the affairs, which under the Basic Law, should be
administered by the Hong Kong SAR on its own, President Jiang
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
