<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Czech Republic to Boost Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma and
his visiting Czech counterpart Vaclav Havel held talks on further
developing bilateral ties here today.
</P>
<P>
There are no contradictions or political disputes between the
two countries, they said, adding that the two countries will
further enhance political and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Havel, who arrived here today for a three-day official visit,
discussed the eastward expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) with Kuchma and spoke highly of the special
partnership accord to be signed between Ukraine and the alliance.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma emphasized that integration with Europe is a strategic
goal of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents also witnessed the signing of bilateral
documents on the avoidance of double taxation and the prevention
of tax evasion, the cooperation in nuclear energy and nuclear
industry, and the fight against organized crimes, terrorism and
drug trafficking. 
</P>
