<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970701.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Hong Kong's Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that the success of Hong Kong, in the final
analysis, is the  work of the Hong Kong compatriots and is
inseparable from the development of the motherland and the support
from the country's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The pioneering and enterprising spirit of the Hong Kong
compatriots "has filled people around the world with deep
admiration," Jiang said at the celebration for the establishment
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong compatriots "will certainly carry forward this
valuable spirit and bring about a better future for Hong Kong," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese in Hong Kong have the ability to run the affairs of
Hong Kong well and they should be confident of that," he quoted
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that since the founding of New China, the Chinese
Government has all along given support for a socially stable and
economically prosperous Hong Kong, and the support has become even
more powerful and effective since the country began to implement
the policy of reform and opening-up in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
With the continuous advance of China's modernization drive,
Hong Kong's economic link with the mainland will become even
closer and its role as a bridge will be increasingly enhanced, he
said. "This in turn will give a stronger impetus to Hong Kong's
economic growth."
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong's success today is also attributable to
a number of other factors, including its advantageous geographical
location, free port policy of complete openness, well-developed
legal system and highly efficient team of civil service, and
effective economic management and civic administration.
</P>
<P>
"These factors will continue to play a positive role after its
return," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong compatriots are known for their glorious tradition of
patriotism, who have made important contributions in the struggle
for national liberation and in the modernization drive of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong compatriots will surely display greater love for
the motherland and for Hong Kong, and take it as their utmost
honor to maintain long-term prosperity and stability in Hong Kong
and safeguard the fundamental interests of the country and the
nation, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
To many foreigners living here, Hong Kong has already become
their home, and it will remain their home in the future where they
can live and work in peace and contentment, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in Hong Kong, everyone will have the chance to
compete on an equal footing and everyone will be entitled to the
rights and freedoms as protected by law, regardless of race and
color.
</P>
<P>
By achieving a negotiated settlement of the Hong Kong question,
the Chinese and British Governments have provided the
international community with an example of peaceful settlement of
historical issues between states, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He thanked those British personages, both within and outside
the government, for their contributions to the smooth transition
of Hong Kong, and expressed confidence that the successful
solution to the Hong Kong question will help strengthen the
friendship between the Chinese and British people.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to reform, opening-up and the modernization drive, China
has witnessed tremendous changes in its economic and social life,
he said.
</P>
<P>
China will unswervingly promote peaceful reunification of the
motherland in accordance with the principle of "one country, two
systems," ensuring a smooth return of Macao and eventually
resolving the Taiwan question, Jiang added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
