<HEADLINE> Performance at Celebration for Establishment of HKSAR to Warm Welcome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The symphony "1997: Heaven, Earth
and Man," composed by Tan Dun, was warmly received today at the
celebration for the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The symphony, which was composed especially for Hong Kong's
return to the motherland and played by noted Violoncellist Ma
Youyou, gives an accurate expression to the themes of the music -
the harmony between heaven, earth and man.
</P>
<P>
Artists from central China's Hubei Province reproduced ancient
Chinese music with serials bells, which date back to more than
2,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Asian Youth Philharmonic Orchestra in Hong Kong
and Jackie Chang, a famous Hong Kong singer, also presented
splendid performances at the celebration.  
</P>
