<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Mozambique Celebrates HK Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy in the
Mozambican capital Maputo held a reception this evening to
celebrate Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The reception began at zero hours on July 1, Beijing time, (6
p.m. local time) when China resumed the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong after 156 years of British colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese embassy prepared two big-screen TV sets to
broadcast the handover ceremony live and held an exhibition of
photographs on Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Mozambican Prime Minister Pascoal
Manuel Mocumbi said that the return of Hong Kong to China is a
great historical event of the century and the Mozambican people
share the joy of Chinese people at this moment.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped Hong Kong would become even more prosperous in
the future.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador Shao Guanfu spoke of the historical
significance of Hong Kong's return and China's policy of "one
country, two systems" towards the administration over the region.
</P>
<P>
The reception was attended by some 200 guests from all circles
of the southeast African country, as well as foreign diplomats and
overseas Chinese. 
</P>
</TEXT>
