<HEADLINE> Tyson Apologizes For Bites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson admitted his bites
in the ring and apologized Monday to Evander Holyfield for his
behavior in their World Boxing Association heavyweight title
rematch on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"I'm here to apologize," said Tyson, who arrived at the MGM
Grand hotel in Las Vegas to read his statement alone.
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who celebrated his 31st birthday on Monday, bit a piece
out of Holyfield's right ear and then bit his left ear before
being disqualified after three rounds in their title bout.
</P>
<P>
"I apologize to the world, to my family, and to the Nevada
State Athletic Commission, which has always treated me fairly,"
Tyson said.
</P>
<P>
Tyson was released from prison on March 25, 1995 after serving
three years of a six-year sentence for rape.
</P>
<P>
The Nevada State Athletic Commission is scheduled to meet on
Tuesday to decide Tyson's fate. 
</P>
