<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT: Land Fund Transferred </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 170 billion Hong Kong
dollars of Land Fund today was handed over to the government of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the People's
Republic of China here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, on
behalf of the Central Government, transferred to Tung Chee Hwa,
the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong SAR, certificates concerning
the Land Fund at a grand celebration party marking the
establishment of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with Annex III to the Sino-British Joint
Declaration, the revenue of the British Hong Kong government
obtained from the trading of land between the time when the
Sino-British Joint Declaration came into effect and June 30, 1997,
minus the average cost of land development, will be divided
equally between the British Hong Kong government and the future
government of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Before the establishment of the government of the Hong Kong
SAR, the Land Fund was managed by holders on trust under the
authorization of the Chinese Government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
