<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Lose 15 Senior Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels, the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), have lost 15 of their
senior leaders including a top medical specialist in an encounter
the rebel flotilla had with the navy off the North-Eastern coast
on Sunday morning, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
While military sources Monday announced the killing of about 40
rebels during the fighting, the LTTE has admitted the loss of only
these 15 senior leaders including a medical specialist, a
political intelligence leader, two senior group leaders and two
women cadres.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday morning, the Sri Lankan Navy destroyed 4 rebel boats
completely while damaging two others.
</P>
<P>
The Navy were also able to arrest several rebel cadres who were
swimming off the coast after their boat was sunk in the
confrontation, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The boats were reported to have been transporting much needed
supplies including medical equipment for the LTTE rebels in the
North from East of the country.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
</TEXT>
