<HEADLINE> Spain, Russia Enter Quarter-finals of Euro Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Spain and Russia each booked
themselves berthes in the quarter-finals of the European
Basketball Championship on Monday after beating Poland and Israel
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Greece and Italy had already claimed their places on Sunday,
while Lithuania and Yugoslavia also entered the top eights.
</P>
<P>
The results of first phase games are carried through to
determine standings in each of the two second phase groups.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Spain, recovered from Sunday's narrow defeat by Italy, to
hammer Poland 104-61, while Russia outclassed Israel 87-69.
</P>
<P>
Italy beat Germany 67-62 to stretch their run of wins to five,
leaving the 1993 winners at the bottom of their second phase group.
</P>
<P>
France were also eliminated after going down 80-71 to Greece,
who together with Italy are the only unbeaten side left in the
competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
