<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Appoints Daughter as Presidential Image Adviser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today officially appointed his daughter Tatyana Dyachenko as his
image adviser, presidential spokesman Sergai Yastrzhembsky said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the president has signed a decree on the
appointment.
</P>
<P>
Dyachenko, 37, graduated from the computer digital control
department of the Moscow State University and played an important
role in his father's re-election last year.
</P>
<P>
In a press interview today, Dyachenko said she will continue to
work on image designing for her father and denied that she can
exert great influence on him. 
</P>
