<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT: Celebration for Founding of HKSAR to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The celebration ceremony for the
founding of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the
People's Republic of China is scheduled to be held at 10 o'clock
this morning at the new extension of the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, who is also general secretary of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, will deliver an
important speech at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, who has just sworn in as the chief executive of
the Hong Kong SAR, will also address the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,600 honored guests, including members of the
Central delegation led by Jiang Zemin, personages of all walks of
life and publc figures in Hong Kong and dignitaries from some
countries, will attend the celebration.
</P>
<P>
The five-star national flag of the People's Republic of China,
and the regional flag of the Hong Kong SAR featured by a bauhinia
in the center hung at the venue of the celebration. There is a
grand view of the Victoria Harbor outside the huge glass panels.
</P>
<P>
Some 170 billion Hong Kong dollars' worth of Land Fund will be
handed over to the Hong Kong SAR government at the celebration
ceremony, which is filled with solemnity and joy.
</P>
<P>
Also at the ceremony, the list of gifts presented to the Hong
Kong SAR government by the Central Government and the 31
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions in China's
interior areas will be announced.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, vivid and exquisite performances will be staged at
the celebration, including the symphony - 1997: Heaven, Earth and
Man - composed by noted Composer Tan Dun and played by Violoncello
Player Ma Youyou.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
