<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Government Marks Hong Kong Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- British Deputy Prime Minister John
Prescott held a reception at the governmet banqueting house here
this afternoon to mark the historical handover of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Some 350 guests from diplamatic corps, business community and
academic fields attended the two-hour long reception and watched
the live coverage of the handover ceremonies held in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Prescott said: "Today is a very
important day to Hong Kong and our relationships with the People's
Republic of China. We have just witnessed an unprecedented event
in modern history."
</P>
<P>
"After 150 years, Hong Kong is now restored to the People's
Republic of China. I would like you all to join me in drinking a
toast to the future of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Prescott, also Secretary of State for Environment, Transport
and the Regions, told Xinhua that with the issue of Hong Kong
peacefully resolved, "now we can begin to further develop our
relations with China."
</P>
<P>
He also noted that he was really impressed with China's
remarkable economic development and now a lot of European
countries including Britain want to upgrade their economic
cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
"China is a very powerful nation, which will play a major part
in the world," he added.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Britain Ma Zhengang, who also attended
the reception, told the gathering "Hong Kong should be a bridge
and not a barrier in the relations between China and the United
Kingdom."
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the conviction that the handover of Hong Kong
will usher in a new period of relations between Britain and China.
</P>
</TEXT>
