<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in UK Celebrates HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Ma Zhengang, Chinese Ambassador to
the United Kingdom, gave a reception here this evening to
celebrate the return of Hong Kong to its motherland.
</P>
<P>
Among nearly 500 guests present were Secretary without
Portfolio Peter Mandelson and other officials of the British
government, diplomatic envoys from various countries in the UK,
and representatives of overseas Chinese and Chinese students.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, the ambassador said that the peaceful
solution of the Hong Kong issue by the Chinese and British
governments had provided an example to solve international
problems left over by history. This was a major contribution to
the world peace and cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ma expressed the conviction that the Hong Kong compatriots,
with the all-out support from China's inland, will create a
brighter future.
</P>
<P>
The reception proceeded in a warm atmosphere. 
