<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thousand in Germany Celebrates Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- About a thousand of people gathered
this afternoon on the riverside of Rhine in Bonn to celebrate
China's resumption of its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Featuring traditional lion dances, song and dance performances
and live broadcasting of the handover ceremonies in Hong Kong, the
celebration was the largest one in Europe which attracted not only
overseas Chinese, but also a number of Germans.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the gathering, Chinese Ambassador to Germany Lu
Qiutian said that Hong Kong's return is a historic event which
marks a great success of the Chinese people's efforts for the
reunify of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jianli, who was born in Hong Kong and now lives in Germany,
said at the ceremony that Hong Kong's return has put an end of a
over-150-year disgrace of the Chinese people. "It is a happy
event for all Chinese."
</P>
<P>
He also noted that Hong Kong's return has only become possible
thanks to a strong motherland. It showed that the fate of Hong
Kong is closely linked to that of its motherland.
</P>
<P>
A fireworks display brought the celebration to its climax at 6
p.m. local time when Hong Kong officially returned to China at
midnight there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
