<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Arts Festival to Mark Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A three-day arts display to mark
the historic occasion of China's resumption of sovereignty over
Hongkong has come to end successfully here today.
</P>
<P>
The display entitled Yan Huang Festival of Chinese Arts, UK's
biggest event to celebrate the handover was featured by some of
the best British - Chinese performance groups including opera,
folk and popular songs, traditional music and classical dance.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of people from various walks of life all over
Britain attended the festival to express their happiness and joy
and also their good wishes to Hongkong people.
</P>
<P>
On the stroke of 5.00 pm on 30 June, the time of the handover
takes place in Hongkong, a fantastic firework display brought the
festival to its climax.
</P>
<P>
"This is the time I have expected for ages," an old overseas
Chinese said. "It is like a child coming back to his mother," the
old man added.
</P>
<P>
Michel Chen, a Hongkong student from London School of Economy,
said: "China's resumption of sovereignty of Hongkong marks the end
of more than 150 years of British rule. The days under the other's
roof have passed." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
