<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrean Students Stage Culture Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Eritrean students in all
parts of the country staged Sunday a parade, showing their
determination to popularize the knowledge of history and culture
of the land.
</P>
<P>
"Eritrea Profile" weekly said in its latest issue that
parade is part of the summer program to teach students to love
the land and to value work ethic in the future.
</P>
<P>
The summer student program has been going on for the last
three years and is now entering its fourth year in Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
According to the Eritrean government, the program has its aim
to put academic theory into practice and to change educational
content into personal experience.
</P>
<P>
Eritrean students are urged to raise the knowledge, capacity
and thinking level for future participation in national
reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean government has spent over 30 million Birr (about
4.2 million U.S Dollars) for the implementation of the program,
the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
