<HEADLINE> Ground Forces of PLA Garrison Heading for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The ground forces of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) Hong Kong Garrison left camps in
Shenzhen at 5:10 a.m. today to head for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the advance troops of the PLA Hong Kong Garrison
already took up the defense duties in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) at zero hour.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 residents in Shenzhen city lined the streets
leading to the customs checkpoints early this morning to see off
the troops.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen has been the main camp of the PLA Hong Kong Garrison.
The troops won the respect and support from people of all walks of
life for their ethics, moral conduct and discipline.  
</P>
</TEXT>
