<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Acting Justice Minister Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today appointed Georgy Kylikov acting justice minister,
Presidential press secretary Sergei Yastrzhembsky told a briefing.
</P>
<P>
Kylikov, first deputy justice minister takes over the post from
Valentin Kovalyov, who has been suspended for a probe after media
published his scandals among naked women.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Lieutenant-General Vladimir Isakov has been
appointed deputy defense minister in charge of logistics and
relieved of his latest post of chief of the logistics staff.
</P>
<P>
According to Yastrzhembsky, reshuffles had been made in the
Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant-General Vladimir Yakovlev has been made commander of
Russian Strategic Missile Forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
